\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you tell me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Robert Purvis Allen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 120 Fenham Hall Drive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Are you married or a widower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I'm a widower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I was married in - 1914. 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now I'm seventy-seven, I was born in 1862 isn't it. No, I'm - 1800 and - 1893. Correct - correct, 1893.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I was born in Jarrow on Tyne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember how many years you lived in the house that you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, now I think that I lived in the house that I was born in - only about three or four year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know where you moved to from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. We moved into a - a house in 26 Grange Road, Jarrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you stay there for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I stayed there right until I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Have you any idea why the family moved from the first house to the house in Grange Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 
We had a shop in - it was a shop and house in Ormond Street in Jarrow, and ironmongery business you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, me father used to work for his father. Now he decided to
 open a shop of his own in Jarrow then of course he shifted to 26 Grange Road. And - we lived there right up 'til I was married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know how old your father was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. He was ninety-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know how old you were when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I would be about forty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did he come from? Had he always lived in Jarrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, he always lived in Jarrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And he always had this ironmongery shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He'd started that from a boy with his dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well he worked with his dad and when he got old enough he started up on his own you see. In this shop, his dad's shop. They give that up. You see, and he started on his own in - in Jarrow an ironmongery business and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember ever having any other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Him having any other jobs? Yes. But I couldn't tell you where he worked but he was - he was a joiner and - he used to tell me that he worked in Middlesborough and that's where he met me mother you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That was a full time job as a joiner was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, yes, as a - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Anything else he had full time job, apart from joinering and the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, just that, was all, that was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember him having any casual jobs or part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, he never had it, no, no, he had enough to do in the business to look after the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He'd never been out of work. Never at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I couldn't tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know how old she was when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I couldn't tell you that because - I couldn't tell you that because I'll tell you why. She
 died - only a lad - because she died when I was three month old. Me mother died when I was three month old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She couldn't have been very young because she had this daughter or about thirteen didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's true, that's true, true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know if she had any jobs before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know if she had any jobs after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No jobs, just - no part time jobs or - helping in the business you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She worked in the shop then did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She was in the - well, they lived in the shop with me father you see. The house was attached to the shop you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So the two of them worked in the shop all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh that's true, that's true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know whether she worked any definite hours in the shop or would she just go in when she could?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well she just went in when she could you see, she would sit in the kitchen and there was the shop there and - you the garden, there was the shop and here was the kitchen you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 Well the
y'd be sitting maybe getting their dinner or something and a customer come in, well if she was near the door she would go into the shop; and serve the customer.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When the children were small did she ever have anybody in to look after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Let's take the house at Grange Street is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Grange Road. Grange Road, Jarrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How many rooms were there in the house part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 There was three bedrooms. And the kitchen. And a sort of back scullery. That was all. And then the shop was attached to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have anybody else living in the house apart from your brothers and sisters and father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No lodgers or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your mother pay anybody to help in the house at all ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was all the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was done at home. Never sent out. There was no launderettes or nothing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did either your father or your mother make any clothes for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me mother used to make clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And she mended them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, that's true, mended the socks and this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have new clothes or sometimes secondhand }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 ones}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We always had new clothes as far as I remember, I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Have you any idea where they were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They were bought at this shop in Ormond Street called Gibbon and Knox.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there special times of the year when you bought new clothes or did you just buy them any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We just bought them any time, any time we needed them we bought them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who mended your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well - me father - he used to - mend his own shoes. And - if there was anything the matter with my shoes he used to repair my shoes and all - he used to repair all the family's shoes as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know where the shoes were bought, were they bought at the same shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Shoes were bought at a shop called Stead and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 Simpson\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 . That's still going. That was in Ormond Street in Jarrow, Stead And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 Simpson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  the shoes were bought there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 house like}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  cleaning, cooking, washing up, lighting fires, decorating, repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Even cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Even cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he do a lot of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. I can tell you all about that because, as I tell you, me mother died when I was three month old. And it was all left to me father. And me father done the cooking and everything. Then we all had scarlet fever. Now they didn't take y
ou to hospital in them days with scarlet fever and me father, he looked after us all with scarlet fever 'cos I remember in my bedroom they got the sheet and put it in carbolic acid or something and used to hang it on the door of the bedroom, you know, and
 disinfect the place and - we all had scarlet fever. Me father done all that. Cook and everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He must have worked very hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 Oh a marvellous man me father, he did, he worked very, very hard.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were very small do you remember him dressing you and bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Yes. Yes. I remember him - is this work - still working like? I can remember when I was a little boy and always wanting to be a sailor, see. So me father bought us a sailor suit. With a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 
sailor\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  collar on and every
thing you know. And they had a two legged stool, you know a stool generally has four legs on and there's two broke off. Well I put this up agen the postel, you know, just layed up against postel, two legs here and the rest was up aside the postel and the 
p
ostel was full of water. So I made myself a little boat of it, a bit of wood and penknife and this that and the other, and I was leaning over into the postel, cos the postel was only - the water was so far from the top and I was learning over playing with
 
this boat and this - were leaning over, this stool come away from me and I fell in the postal. Head first. And me father see - he was in the kitchen, I was in the back yard - and he happened to see me through the window, legs sticking out the postel, he c
omes and pulls us out. I always remember that. I was lucky, lucky he was there or else I'd have been drowned, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, he hadn't time for anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No time. No time for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he ever take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 
He took one - he took us out - he took me out when I got older but not when I was very, very young. When I - when - when I'd be about twelve or thirteen he'd take us out but when I was very, very young he - he never took us out. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Now do you know where I used to sleep. Now he hadn't time to put me to bed. These were the days when the shop opened at - about eight o'clock in the morning and never closed 'til eleven o'clock at night. And he hadn't time to put me to bed
, he used to lay me on the counter in the shop. Remember that quite well. And of course my daughter says I've had an easy life, I've a daughter you see. And - he used to lay me on the counter. And he used to cover me up with brown paper what he used to wr
ap the paper parcels in for the customers, that was me - that was me blankets. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 
Because how I knew all about this - when I - shop was shut and everything and he put me to bed I must have been dead asleep you see, he put me to bed and when I woke up in the mo
rning, a little pair of short trousers and put them on, put me hand in me pocket and there used to be ha'pennies in, a few ha'pennies. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
And the customers must have put them in me pocket you see. Yes. That's - that's that - that's how I got rich, aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were a bit older and your dad took you out, where did he take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
When I got a bit older? Oh yes, yes, when I got older I used to take - of course he only had time off a little bit on a Wednesday you see. Because he used to have a quite a l
ot of work in the shop and - any time on the Wednesday half day off he used to take us out, he used to take me out anyway to Carlisle and different places like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any jobs that you had to do regularly while you were at home before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Now that's not me father's fault, it's my fault because I was always an ambitious chap and - I wanted a job so - along the street there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 bloke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  - chap had a shop they called the McNeis
h they were Scotch people. So I went along and asked if they wanted and errand boy you see. So - he says you look a likely look lad, yes, you see. So he said, well he says, I want an errand, can you carry bread, let's feel your muscles? And - you know put
 your arm out and feel your muscles. Yes, I got the job carrying bread. And used to take bread to his customers and carry it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old were you when you got that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I'd be about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I used to - go there when I was - coming away from school. Yes, when I come away from school I used to go there and deliver his bread.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 From about four o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 But I used to go home and get me tea - about half past four. Used to go to the shop about ha
lf past four, used to get the bread and take it, put a big basket on me arm and carry it round different places. And - on the weekend - he had a horse and van. It was two brothers ran this business and he had a horse and van and - on the weekend he used t
o
 get me to come with him in his van for to deliver the bread to shops and this that and the other. Well there's one time I was with him in the van, this is a funny things this now. There's one time I was with him in the van and - he went to Bolden collier
y
, you know where Borden colliery is? He went there, yes, he went to Bolden colliery. And before he started to deliver the bread he went into a pub. And I was sitting on the van, the bread van with a horse and - a bread van was a pretty big van you know an
d
 a place for two to sit and the wheels in the centre, anyway he went into this pub - and he was in such a long time and I was sitting on the van. And - I says to myself, this'll not pay the rent. And I went into the pub and he was drunk. So I says to him,
 
Mr McNeish. I says, are you - are you coming home and delivering. So he says, you get outside, he says, and sit on the van 'til I come out, you see. So I says to myself, I says, I'm not going to sit here and - so I gets the reins of the horse and I drove 
t
he horse back to the shop in Jarrow to his brother's. Told his brother that he was drunk you see. So he says - could you take the horse to the stable and take its harness off and give it it's hay and all this that and the other, he says, because I can't l
e
ave the shop you see. Bit difficulty. I says, yes. And that's why I took the horse to the stable and - took its harness off, give it its water made its bed and everything and - when I went to work the next night, that's when I come from school, got me tea
 
and I went to work. Stewart they call him, McNeish, this one that - who had the van. He gets a hold of me and he says, who's running this business, you or I? You see, and I'm just kid. Well, I says, I expect you're running the business. Why? Well, he says
,
 what's the idea, he says, of taking - well, I says, you were drunk. So he says, well that's got nothing to do with you, you see. I says, what did you want me to do, sit there all night waiting you up for morning, no fear of me doing that you see. So he s
ays, well you're finished, sacked. So I says -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So that was the end of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
No, half a minute. He says, you're sacked. I says, that's all right. So his brother turns round then and he says, you - you'll - they called me Bob like, he said, Bob, ta
ke no notice of him, he says, you're not sacked at all, he says. They had a bit argument and of course it all cleared up and oh I still - I still worked there. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of hours did you work normally on a Saturday and Sunday for this baker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
I didn't work on a Sunday. I worked on a Saturday. I'll tell you - on a Sunday - I was stopping like animals and all this I used to go along and see the horse was all right on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Saturday. I never worked on a Saturd
ay, I went along to the shop and I used to talk to the young lady what used to serve in the shop, the assistant. Her and I were pretty sweet you know, and were - you know. And I used to go along and talk to her. But I never worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And in the week you worked from about half past four 'til about when?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh from half past four 'til - about eight o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I got the large sum of four and six per week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I thought it was a good wage. That was all pocket money, I never give me father nothing. He wouldn't take it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Ah well - I used to spend it on sweets and - I used to go to the theatre. I don't think there was any pictures in th
em days. No, there wasn't any pictures in them days, I used to go to the Theatre Royal. And - go there and see what was on there and - sometimes there'd be a waxworks }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 show}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  come to the place, used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you feel about your employer, this man Stuart McNeish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well - the two brothers, Stuart, the one that - used to go and deliver the bread, I used to go in the van this Saturday and I didn't care nought for him at all, but his brother, I used to like his brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 Oh I liked the work all right, yes, yes, I liked the work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
As long as I was getting money that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did it make you think anything different about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, well I had - me, I had a very difficult time at school, no. It didn't. I would rather work than go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was that always true or did you only start thinking that after you got the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I never liked school. I never liked school, and I can tell you why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any other part time jobs like that before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, that was the only job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old were you when you had this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I'd only be about eleven or twelve I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you do any particular jobs in the house, like fetching coal and cleaning shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Never cleaned the shoes, no. Brought coal, brought coal in. I brought coal, I used to go for coal. The coal wasn't delivered them days, used to go to the coal depot with a barrow and get a hundredweight of coal and pull it along 
and put it in the coal outside the door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any other jobs at home that you used to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. I used to help me father in the shop, that was home. Helping me father in the shop. And - me father used to grind scissors, he was a locksmith. A cutler an
d - he used to sharpen swords and he used to grind scissors. He used to do soldering. Now I used to help him with all that. And he showed me how to solder and how to do this and how to do that and how to do other. Well - when he was busy serving customers
 
and customer come in and wanted - a handle solder - soldered on a teapot or anything like that, he used to fetch it into me and say, Robert, he called me Robert, he says, Robert, would you solder that on? You see, and I used to do that you see, jobs like 
that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 These two jobs of fetching the coal and helping in the shop, did you carry on with these after you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I still carried on after I left school. 'Til I was sixteen. I carried on 'til I was sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That was two years, were you fourteen when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Left school, left school. No, I - I didn't like school and - me father - used to send us to school, you had to start school at eight o'clock in the morning. And of course by the time he opened his shop he hadn't
 time to come and look what after me whether I went to school or not you see. And he used to come in and - and he'd say, Robert, it's time you were at school. I says, I'm late now. Well, he says, you should have went before, you see, and of course I used 
t
o go to school late you see. I used to get the stick every morning, that's why I never liked school. And of course I got hardened to it, you see. Late again, hold out your hand, you used to hold out your hand and you'd cane - the cane you see. Me hand got
 that hard I didn't care, I didn't care. You see. I was glad when I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were getting ready for school when you were quite young did your older brothers and sisters used to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The - at that time when I went to school and m
e older sister was away, she was married but the - the other sister she used to - do what she could. What she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were fairly small do you remember the older ones helping the younger ones with all kinds of things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Like at meal times?-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well no - yes and no. The older one I don't remember her doing very very much with the younger ones, she helped all she could. But me father used to do most of the work, me father used to do - me father used to do all the cooking, 
I remember him doing all the cooking. And of course being inquisitive I asked him, what's the matter with Emily doesn't cook? Oh, he says, she cannot cook. You see, he'd do it himself, me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That would be much quicker for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's true, 
that's true. He used to cook the Sunday's dinner at Sunday, make the Yorkshire pudding and all, me father. Oh he were good man, me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did anyone put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you share the bedroom with your brothers or with all the family or how many bedrooms were there to share between all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I - I used to sleep with me brother and me father, three in a bed. Three in a bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did the other brother sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
The other brother used to sleep in a - another small room we used to call the shanty. He used to sleep in another small room and me sister slept in the next room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So there were three bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 One for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  and two for the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's correct. That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The room we bathed in - was the kitchen downstairs in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 galvanized}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  bath 'cos there was no bathroom. You see, had a galvanised bath on the floor, just bath yourself in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well me father was very strict about that, he would see that you had bath every week. Remember that, bath every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was there a special day for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, me - be Friday. Bath Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All the family used to get bathed and father was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  strict - particular about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have special days for putting clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 After your mother died who used to do the washing in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me younger sister. She used to - she used to do the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was there a special room where the family used to eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, Just in the kitchen. There was no special dining room - nothing like that, just the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever eat in another room or always in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Always in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where was the cooking done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The cooking was done in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of thing did you cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We just cooked on an ordinary fire. Just an ordin
ary coal fire - coal fire. I can remember that quite well. Coal fire because when I was - just a youngster me father was in the shop, there was nobody in the kitchen and had one of these hobs in front of the fire with a teapot on. And I was crawling along
, just a kid like, and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 knocked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 it over and - the hot teapot fell on me and burnt all me back and you know I went screaming in the shop to me father. And - he had to take us to the hospital, I can remember that. Back was all blisters and arms were. So you 
see what a job me father had. Oh.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When did you usually have your breakfast, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We had our breakfast about - be about half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who used to sit down for that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I remember, yes, I can remember me two brothers, myself and me father. Younger sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you usually eat or drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
We had tea and always had bacon and egg. Because I'm - I can remember me father, if we had no bacon, maybe he'd go to the pantry and there's no bacon, he'd say to me, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 Robert}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , go and get a pound of bacon. And he'd give us sixpence, it was sixpence a pound. And I used to go there. Always had that. Well fed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever have any different breakfasts on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. Always bacon and egg. No cornflakes, or nothing like that. Nothing like them, I don't yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What time did you used to have your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We used to have our dinner at twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were all of you there or only some of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 There were only some of them there. And - the dinner was never cooked. They used to go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 cook}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 shop. And they used to get one of these - what - what do they call them? Hocks I think. You know, pigs - leg, you know, sort of right up its leg, a hock they used to call it. And - me father used t
o get that and he used to put it and give us that and bread and butter and that's what we used to get for our dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have anything to drink with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, you had tea. Tea. Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So just pork hock and bread and butter and tea?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did the others manage for their dinner, the ones that weren't there, who wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, me older sister - me older sister wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Because she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, she was married, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They were there and me brothers were there, they had just the same. This - this -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 ever have a different dinner like on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, on a Sunday used to have roast beef and Yorkshire pudding and potatoes and cabbage and all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  sort of - me father used to cook that. As far as I ever know, always remember me father, he - he cooked that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you call the evening meal, was that your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, you had tea. You had tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What time did you have your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You had your tea about - five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was that usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - some of us would like a bloater herring, someone would like a kipper and - someone would like a teacake and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you choose what you had then every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh 
you could choose what you had, yes, you could choose what you had you see. Say, what do you want for your tea? Father - me father used to say - what do you want for your tea. Oh, I says, I'd like a two eyed steak, you see, kipper. Well, he says, go and ge
t
 yourself one, and give you the money you see, I'd go and get one. And me sister - me sister would say, I would like a bloater, you see. And ask them, the - the people at the fish shop for a one with roe in, she used to say pot bellied bloater, you know, 
one with roe in. Right, so I used to go and get that for our tea. And for our supper, fish shop.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What time did you have supper then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We had our supper about - nine o'clock, nine 'til half past nine. Fish shop were - go and get a penn'orth of eac
h that was a fish and chips for tuppence you see. Used to get - used to get that, we had that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All the family had that did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All the family had that, fish and chips.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And all the family sat down to tea together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All the - that's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any different teas or suppers on different days, what about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh you had different on a Sunday. - Sunday was a special day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What would you have for Sunday tea then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For Sunday tea we used to have - we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 used }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
to buy cakes, you never baked any cakes and me sister, younger sister, she couldn't bake and me father, he - I never seen him bake any cakes or nothing like that. And we used to go and buy cakes and used to have a special tea on a Sunday, used t
o be biscuits and cake and cheese. Boiled egg. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Your father didn't bake his own bread did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he make any jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Or bottle any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Make any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Brew any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he grow any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. We had no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So he bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He bought them all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were they fresh or dried or tinned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Fresh. Fresh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 fresh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Always fresh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And fruit as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Fruit always fresh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you keep any pigs or chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. Nothing. Nothing, no animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How many times a week would you say you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I think myself we used to eat meat every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You always had bacon didn't you for a start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
We always had bacon. We had bacon, then for our dinner we had this hock. We had that and sometimes - I remember - - me going for chops and - going for liver, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You had plenty of meat then didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, we had plenty of meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No tinned meat. Never had no tinned meat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever get any extra meat from poaching, things like rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, but
 I'll tell you what we did have meat from - I used to keep rabbits. A lad, you see, they used to keep rabbits. And they sometimes used to kill one of them. And - I - I didn't agree to it like you see but me father was - that's a - a nice rabbit, I think I
'll have that for our dinner you see. I says, oh you're not going to kill that. So me older brother would say, no use crying, we're going to have it. And he used to get it and kill it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who used to look after the rabbits then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember seeing your father having less food to let the children have more? Or did he have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, all had about the same, you can all eat your fill. We never - never had any trouble over that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you always choose what you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did your dad say if you didn't eat all you had on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He used to - tell you to eat it and if you didn't eat it all he'd want to know what was the matter you didn't eat i
t. And he'd ask you if you were ill. Says, no I'm not ill I - I - I just can't - I just can't eat it. Shy can't you eat it? Well I don't like it. You see. What do you like? You see, and you would tell him and then he would try and get you that for the nex
t day you see. Yes, he's very good like that, very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt would you just ask for someone to pass it to you or would you reach out and get it or did you have to wait until it was passed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh no, reach out and get it that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Sometimes if you're hungry. Got any more of that? Yes. And get it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No special way, just
 used to have to hold it in your proper hand. Oh no. Had to hold it properly, yes, we held it properly you used to have to hold it in your - your knife in your right hand and your fork in your left hand. And he seen to that. You see, because - I was given
 - to be left handed, you see, and played football and that left footed. Now he seen that, I never noticed that myself but he seen that and he'd say to me, you've got your knife in your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 
ringhand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , put it in your other hand. You see, and it was only natural. 
The next day I would come down and - they'd tell as I'd be left handed, I would get me knife in me left hand again. And he would notice it straight away. He'd say, put your knife in your other hand. You see, now I found that very good after I'd grow up an
d
 went to serve me time and that. Now I can use both hands, yes, you see, write with me right hand and write with me left hand, both hands. And at work sometimes - in the engineering factory - there was jobs you could do far better awkward jobs with your l
eft hand, you see, and I could use both hands, you see, found that was great advantage then. In later life, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you bring toys or a book to the table at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, he wouldn't let you do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 When you could leave the table?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6641988\charrsid15818556 
Well as soon as you ever finished what you had to eat you could leave the table yourself and - just - say excuse me and - leave the table, that was all.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you always sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who used to serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who got served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The oldest son used to get served first. Then work right out until it come - it come to muggings, me, the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were very small before you could sit at the table to you remember where you used to sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, I used to sit on the floor.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And who fed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 One of me sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was your father an easy man to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 A very easy man to talk to, oh yes, he'd - listen to you, take notice of what you said, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Would you call him an affectionate person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Very affectionate person I'd call him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 If you had any worries could you share them with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. You could share them with him but he - he never used to ask you if you had any worries, he'd try to 
bear them all himself, he'd never ask you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did your father expect you to behave towards him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well he used to expect you for the respect him. And - talked to one for another and - if he had - if he was talking to anyone he never - expected you or wanted you to butt in or anything like that you see, keep you in your place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Did he bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways, were there things that you had to do and things that you didn't have to do in dealing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
