\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - when he was working he was - he'd be the same as me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 
When he was working, we all worked for our living, we're all labour men, labour for our living but when he was 
working - his - fellow member and brother of the joiner society or something like that, and they were on piecework and the foreman come in and asked them, how much will do this job for? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
And - the - the piece clerk it was come in and I want you to do this w
ork for - job for me for so and so. He'd go to a chap what's in the same union as him and ask - how much will you do this job for? The piece clerk would go and ask him you see, how much he'd do the job for. To he - this other chap. So he'd say, how much i
s
 Mr Allen doing it for? That's me father you see. So and so. He says, oh well I'll do it for a half a crown cheaper than him. You see. And of course after that Labour party, no. Conservative party. Well I - I'm the same. I was the same. I was - working at
 Palmers in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 Jarrow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  when he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556  were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  open, you'll not remember Palmers at Jarrow, I don't suppose you'll have heard of them even. Yes. Well when I was working there - I was a same as big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 
Mitchell\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  plating first and there were - and the piece clerk said, how muc
h for that job? Tuppence for so and so and so and so. Right. Goes to the chap at the next bench, how much? So he says, how much does Bob Allen want? Oh, so and so. Oh, he says, I'll do it a couple of bob cheaper than him. You see, the piece clerk come and
 told me. So of course I reported him at the union you see and - nothing - nothing become of it you see, so I would never vote Labour me on account of it, that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember your dad voting in an election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Before 1918? Oh yes, oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know whether or not he voted Conservative then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, he would, as I knew, I knew he voted Conservative man you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know if your father - he didn't work for anybody did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh no, he was self employed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your father belong to a political party, was he a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 A member of what - the Conservative party? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he work for the Conservative at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, he hadn't - he'd stick bills in the window and this, that and the other but he never had time, he was too busy in the shop.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he do anything in the way of political activity apart from election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He - he never done anything, never done anything, he - he hadn't time you see. His full time was the shop. You see, serving in the shop.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Didn't he have any spare time at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Very little. Serving in the shop. Then while he's serving in the shop - the people come in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 fetching}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  jobs in you see, they want this soldered, they want their scissors sharpened, they wa
nt their best saw sharpened. And when the shop shut - he had to get stuck into that work and get it done for the next day for them to come for it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When he did have spare time how did he spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not spare time. Well that's about - that'
s about all he did, he would just go and have a walk round the town or - on a Wednesday he would take me to Carlisle or something like that. That was all. Had a walk round the town, very seldom away anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What time did he normally finish in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I've seen him - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  'til eight or nine o'clock maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was that common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That was common then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Would he almost always stay at home after he'd finished work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, he stayed at home, he used to be tired, he used to stay at home, see him sitting down reading a paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he ever go to any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Never at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Never. Never I've seen him in a - no clubs at all, well he's the same as me, I don't believe in these working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  clubs or nothing, I'm more the - the only clubs I ever went to was when I retired. Sixty-five, you know, old peoples club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was he keen on any sport, did he take part in any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He never took part in anything but he used to be interested in me taking - football and things like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he ever go to any horse races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Never bet a horse in his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he belong to any savings clubs, boot club, sick club, funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, boot club. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How di
d you get on with your brothers and sisters, you didn't get on so good with your eldest brother, what about the other three, how did you get on with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me brother - the next one to me, not the eldest one, the next one to me I got on very well with
 him and him and I got on well. And also got on well with the two sisters. All quite all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was there anyone of the three that you were very close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, the brother next to me, he was a nice chap. He never - got his - on in the world as w
ell as what I did which was very sorry for because - my ambition was always to be - an engineer. Now his ambition - was the same. He'd made a craftsman. And - he - he was - cleverer than me in a lot of things. He could - go down to the river and see a boa
t going out and he could just sketch it on a postcard and he could come home and - draw it and paint it. And it was exactly the same as the one he'd seen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 Very, very clever. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now I couldn't do nothing like that. No, he was very clever at making model ships. He used to make model ships, he made a - you've heard of the Mauritania. When the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 Mauritania}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 was about at Swann and Hunters there he made a model of that. And - he put the keel plate down made of tin which me father had in the shop and a soldering iron and
 this that and the other you know. He done all that and he made this ship and it was being as big as that. Four foot long and - he - made turbines out of tin blades you know, this, that and the other. And he made the boiler and he made this ship and it wa
s a very good model of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 Mauritania}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
. And he used to take them to Jarrow Park and - he had a blow lamp in it - in the boiler, and he used to go about the park. Lovely - lovely job it was. Now he never got anywhere. Now - me -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who did you play, with, your brothers and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh no, when I went out to play I - you know, you'd - have a mate. You know, somebody - somebody from the street you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did you play usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Played in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The back or the front?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In the front. 'Course there wasn't the traffic there is now, no motor cars nor nothing like that you know, played in the front street.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Mostly football. And - blind man's buff - lying in somebody's garden and tying a bit of black thread to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 knocker,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 lying in the garden and knock at the door and when a woman opened the door let the thread go slack as she opened the door and nobody there and - she shut the door again. As soon as she shut the door we'd wait a few moments, knock again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you get as dirty as you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Oh yes, never - never - oh no, no, no. Used to get - come and tore a hole in your pants or something like that, he used to get on to you about it you see. Look at them trousers
, he says, I just got them the other day, look as those ruined. Well, I says, I'll sew them up. I sewed them up myself. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you play with anybody you wanted to or did your dad sometimes say don't play with him or don't play with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You 
could play with anyone you wanted to but he didn't like you to play with Catholics. Aye, I don't know whether you're a Catholic or not but - aye, well I'll tell you why. I'll tell you why. Because he was born in Dublin. And - his father belonged Sheffield
. But he was in business}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15818556  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
and all and he come to Dublin and he opened a shop there, an ironmongers shop and that in Dublin. And - of course he went to Church of England you see. And of course when they come out of church my father says when he was a lad, whe
n he come out of church there's some of these great big Irishmen got hold of him and held him over the River Liffey. Aye. They was going to drop him in because he was a Protestant. And he never forgot that He never forgot that, he told me to have nothing 
to do with Catholics or nothing. Oh aye, aye. And now of course I was brought up like that you see, you know, it's always remained in me. I think there's as good - I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 there\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  as good as Catholics as what there is Protestants, but it's always - kept in me, now I'll tell you a funny thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 About that}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
. I was foreman at - in an oxygen company. The British Oxygen Company had a place in Jarrow and I was foreman for them at the Jarrow branch. And - there was a - my wife - sister - her husband, he was a Catholi
c. And he was a fitter. And he was out of work. And my missus told me about it, my missus was a very good woman and everything like that, and she told me about it and she said, Bob, how about so and so, she says, he's - he's a fitter. She says, I don't kn
o
w, well he's the same sort of fitter as you are or not. I says, I'm not a fitter, I'm a seaman engineer you see, you know. Oh well, she says, you're at British Oxygen, she says. I says, yes, I'm foreman maintenance man at the British Oxygen. And she says,
 
do you think you could give him a job? You see, I - I started him maybe. So I says - tell your sister for to send to him along. Come along to the house and I'll have a talk to him you see. So anyway, he come along to the house and talking, and - I said, w
here did you serve your time? So he says, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 Haggey's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 Ropey, you see. Oh well, I says, it's a different class of machinery altogether, I says, at the British Oxygen, I says, there's air compressors and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 acetylene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  compressors and oxygen compressors and - well,
 he says, we hadn't any compressors there but, he says, I think I can manage it, he says. Well, I said, all right, you seem an intelligent enough sort of a chap. I says, all right. So I give him a job. So - first week I took it you know, just fitting on n
u
ts and bolts and all this that and the other. There was a particular job come up - and - there was eight hundred - bottles of oxygen - hundred feed bottles of oxygen had to go to South Africa. And they had to be pumped up one night and had to go to South 
A
frica the next day you see. So this chap, he was on shift this night and what was running, there was just a big - air compressor making this oxygen in a big - oxygen - small oxygen compressors cylinder, you see, four thousand pound. But anyway, to cut a l
ong story short - one o'clock in the morning there's a knock at my door. So me a sleepyhead - never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 bothered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
, I didn't bother. So the missus - put her head out the window. How's that? So they says, Mr Allen's got to come down to work. So of course the missus knew nothing about it, she's -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 nudged}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 me with her elbow like you know the way it is. I says, what's the matter? She says, you've got to go down to work? Work, what for? She says, I don't know, a chap's down the chaps out there. So I puts me head out of th
e window, I says, what's the matter? So he says that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 something\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 gone wrong with the oxygen compressor. And he says, the chap that's on - he says, he doesn't seem to be able to manage the job. And he says, you know the cylinders has }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
