ed, this old man Johnson. And - I said, how long has this been knocked about? So he says, it broke down about twelve o'clock. Twelve o'clock I says, half past one now, I says, it's only half an hour's job, that. Putting that in. Well, he says, I canna get
 
it in, he says. Like putting a fibre into the - into the cylinder. He says, I canna get it in. So I says, you know what you want to do, I says, you want to say Hail Mary three times, I says, and it have gone in. Being a Catholic you see. Oh. Well - then I
 
just goes to the store and got a fibre and - mucked in and I put it in myself you see. Started the thing away, well it was all running and everything, I says, there you are. I says, you should have said Hail Mary three times, you believe in all the Cathol
i
c businesses and that. So, he says, what makes you mention now, what makes you mention that. Well I says, what - why didn't you get the job done, I says, you're a fitter aren't you, you're supposed to have it out. So just went away with that, I felt annoy
e
d, of course I went to bed again. When I come in the next morning - there's a - when the manager come in, chap called Hunt, he ring me up - I was in the factory, he's in the office. He rung me up, had to go and see him. So I went and see him like and - he
 
says, I see you were called out in the middle of the night. I says - what was idea of that? See. He says, what was the matter - what was the matter with the shift engineer on the - on the shift. He said, was he feeling bad or did he drop down dead or some
t
hing like that? I says, no. Well what was the matter? I says, it seems that he couldn't do the job, he sent out for me. Oh, he said. He said, send him here. And of course I never told anyone you see, how did the manager get to know you see. He get to know
 
off - off my report you see, you had to report hourly. He says, send him in. So I sent him in. And he says, you stop here and all. Stop there. So he says to this bloke, he says, how was this compressor stopped, a couple of hours last night and why did you
 
have to send out for Mr Allen here? Well, he says, I've had - I haven't had a great experience with them, he says, and he says, I had a bit trouble and, he says - he said, don't beat about the bush, say that you couldn't do the job. He told him straight. 
A
nd he said, lookey here, he says, see all them fellows walking about up and down there, he says, they are all out of work. He says, they can't get a job. And, he says, if you don't attend to your work, and look after things better, he says, you'll join th
at queue. And that's all he said to him. He said, but told him, if he didn't pull his socks up well he'd sack him. Yes. And - that's just my joke you know, saying Hail Mary three times.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you belong to any youth organisations, anything like the Boy Scouts or any youth clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes. I belonged to the boy Scouts.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
No, that was all, the Boy Scouts, there was the Boys Brigade first and I would never join that group. When the Scouts come on I joined the Boy Scouts then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were at school did you have any hobbies, did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, I used to keep rabbits. Yes, and I was greatly interested in electricity. Dry batteries and I used to make dry batteries. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 I've a great hand for electricity; now.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any other hobbies? Gardening, stamp collecting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no hobbies like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 that, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 no gardening or stamp collecting or nothing like that. Mostly all engineering - that - that was my main hobby, engineering, I used to buy all engineering books and read about ships, ships. Ships, electricity and rabbits.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you like fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Fishing - yes, that was big hobby of mine but still is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any other sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 football,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  that was all. Football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 theatre,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  did you go to any concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Yes, I used to like to go to the music hall, Empire at Newcastle every Saturday night I used to like to go there. And theatres. And I used to occasionally go to a dance, I liked going to a dance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You used to get a ha'penny a week pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I used to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 sixpence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  a week pocket money. Sixpence a week I used to get - that. That's beside - I used to get a ha'penny a day. I used to get a ha'penny a day for sweets, then it's - on the weekend I used to get sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  you spent that on sweets and the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Sweets, yes, yes, sweets too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What happened if your dad was ill or if ever he had to stay in bed for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, yes - there - me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 sister}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  used to - she was never married now and she looked after us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any close relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Close relatives? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your dad have any particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did he meet his friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He had - some people, they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 corn merchants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 you know, business the same as him and that - that was his particular friend. He never made a - a great to do with any lot of friends or nothing like that, just - they used to come into the shop and talk to him you see and - that was that.
 Never used to go out with them or nothing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they ever come into the house or just in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Just in the shop. Never into the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know how often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh no, maybe every week and - maybe is - that - that's the most that they meet, once a fortnight or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they get offered anything to eat or drink when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about neighbours, were there any particular neighbours who used to call in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well they never had anything to do with the neighbours much because the neighbours were shops, all shops you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your dad ever go out to visit his friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, he used to go out visit his friends and also me father - I had an aunt, that was me father's wife'
s sister lived in Middlesborough and he used to often go there and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 see them}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
What kind of amusements did your dad have when he went out to visit his friends or his wife's sister, what kind of things do you think they did?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They just used to talk, that was all. Never used to go out, just sat and talked that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Some people divide society into different social classes or groups, do you think of some people belonging to one social class or another before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you couldn't say your family belonged to any particular class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well, the only - the only group or class - I would say were - belonged to were - the middle class I would say. Because - the majority were labouring class and - nav
vies and all this that and the other, well of course - ore you see, in the next class, like - call it the middle class you see, shopkeepers and people like that you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any other people other than shopkeepers you'd put in the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, schoolteachers and - people like that. Or anybody that - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 
trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , anybody that had a trade or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What sort of people belonged to the other classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh well - now, I may be wrong but - anyone that's a 
labourer, you see. Now I get wrong about this off the daughter and everybody else. No, but anyone that's a labourer now, well anybody can be a labourer. You see, I think they've }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 got}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  no ambition, you see. They're just like driftwood, you've still got no amb
ition at all anybody give 'em a job, shoveling ship or out like that they would do it you see. And - I've got no use for them, for people like that you see. That's my impression.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you brought up to treat any kind of people differently from anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you ever taught to touch your cap or show respect in some way to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes. Yes. Ladies. All }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 ladies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Even labourer's wives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. All ladies. All ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you mean all women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes all women all women yes all women \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was there anyone that you had to call sir or master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, no. No. No. Me father, always no sirs, the same as you, you are just as good as them, no sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember anyone showing particular respect to your dad by calling him sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who would say that to him, who would call him sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Someone that had an axe to grind. Somebody that wanted something for nothing or somebody wanted to sell something. Commercial traveller.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He'd be all creepy would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Commercial traveller come in wanting to sell him something, yes sir, no sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When he got annoyed I suppose he'd call him madam would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Might do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who were the most important people in Jarrow at that time, in your opinion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I thought the most important person in Jarrow was me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You said the Mayor was the most important person in Jarrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who else was important do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4349456\charrsid15818556 the police}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 . The Mayor and the police. That's about all I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you meet them, did you ever come into contact with the Mayor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Mm, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 m.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I come in contact with the police in all cases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Friendly contact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - friendly contact, th
e police is all right, they done - they done they're job. I'll tell you a funny thing about the police. When I was courting - me young lady, there were a shop door, we lived in the house at back of the shop you see, we had to go through the shop to get in
t
o the house. Well our shop door there was a - an alcove you know, you've seen it. Well I was standing in the alcove, oh be about half past nine or something like that. Talking to this young lady you see. Policeman come along and - put his sights on me. Co
m
e on now, what're you doing. None of that. So I says, who're you talking to? So he says, I'm talking to you, he says, come on along out. I says, I'm not getting out. He says, if you don't get out, he says, I'll come and put you out. I says, you'll do noth
ing of the sort, I - I live here. I says, my father pays his rent and rates for this. He says, oh you live here, he says, I'm very sorry.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why do you pick out the Mayor and the police as being very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well the police looks after you. And - the Mayor - well he's - he's an important man and - of the town isn't he. That's - that's }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 why}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Would you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 say}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  the shopkeepers were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I wouldn't say they're important, they're important for a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who did the shopkeepers spend their time with, the shopkeepers that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well - the shopkeepers that I knew in Jarrow they was just - spent most of their time in the shop you see, they never had any - never seen any social activity, no, they was all shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know about the social activities of the clergymen, do you know who they spent their time with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Schoolteachers - schoolteachers and they spent their leisure time in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 
\endash most of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  them went to dance, I met quite lot of schoolteachers at dances and this that and other. And of course - kept theirself to theirself, in the class, one class that's all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there different kinds of people who went to the Church of England, the chapel and the Roman Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh, three different - three different kinds of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well the Catholics, they go to church, they come out of church and they can go in the boozer, get drunk or out like that. Commit sins. And - go to church the next Sunday and confess their sins to their Father and their sins is forgiven. Well }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  absolutely dead rot, that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you see them doing that, did you know this happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I know it happened, I know it happened. I know it happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did it happen when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
It happened when I was a boy. I drunk holy water when I was a boy, me. You know, they used to have in the Catholic chapel in Jarrow, used to have a font there where they christen the babies in - holy water. And, me, a lad like - th
irteen or twelve, used to go in there if were thirsty and we used to go and get a basin and drink the holy water, and we used to think we were doing good. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the Anglicans then, Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I've found out in the Church of England - a lot of them are }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 
hypocrites}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  who just go there - for to mix with people what they think is - going to do them some good, you know. Higher class people you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where would you put the Catholics, are they not high class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well the Catholics, yes. Yes, yes. The Catholics who - Father - I call him Father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Hooligan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 or Father Machon or somebody like that, they'll come to your house and they'll - they'll come to this house, thought I was a Catholic or something. He says, I've come to bless th
e house. You see, knocked at the door, come to bless the house, you know. I says, the house is already blessed, I says, it won't do any better by you blessing it, I says, you're not the Almighty. I says, the only people that can bless this house is Almigh
ty God and, I says, you're not him. That was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the chapel people then, how did they fit into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now I like the chapel people better than church. I think the chapel people -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I mean chapel people in general when you were a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes, well that's what I said, I like the chapel people - the chapel people the best, they were - seemed to me to be - had no axe to grind and they were very sociable with one another and - some of them were in business you see and - one I remember quit
e well, he was a dentist and - I used to go to his - place if I had - me teeth was dirty or anything like that, and asked his advice which he would give you and - there were - you know, the same as we were, decent sort of people, chapel people like.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you get many labourers going to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Labourers? Oh well, yes, I daresay. Yes, yes, well I - I couldn't tell you that now}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15818556  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 to be honest with you I couldn't tell you that, I didn't know many, I didn't know of any, they were mostly shopkeepers or dentists and - solicitors or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Where you lived did all the people in the middle class have the same standard of living or where there different groups with in the middle class group which you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, they seemed to have all the same standard of living as what we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you describe a family that you knew - a family of a labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, well there's a neighbour next to us, and - her husband was a labourer. And - he couldn't get a job and - with a lit
tle money she had she opened a shop, you see, and in this shop she started to make pies and peas and all this that and the other. And he - kept these Australian rabbits, you know, white rabbits. And he used to sell them to the butcher for about five bob a
 
piece and he used to breed them and sell them for five bob apiece and of course the butcher used to sell them for a seven and six or eight bob. And - that's how they lived. Now he was a labourer and he couldn't get a job and that's what - they used to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you think he was typical of labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, well no. No, I wouldn't say he was typical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know any labourers families that were more typical then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Now half a minute. Yes. I knew another labouring family and - they come to 
Jarrow because they couldn't get work in Birmingham and they come from Birmingham. And - he was a labourer in a tube works, made copper tubes in Birmingham and he was a labourer there and they couldn't get work, then they come to Jarrow. So he got a job l
abouring at a brass furnaces at Palmers, Jarrow, and - he was a decent sort of a chap him, he - worked at the brass furnaces labouring, had twenty-one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 bob}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  a week. And - the brass furnaces shut down and he got the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 sack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
. And he went as far away as Ashingdon and worked at the pit, labouring at the pit. And - that's typical I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 of house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  did they live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They lived in a - in a pitman's house you know, pit house. Used to have to go upstairs to the bedroom, by a ladder. Yes. Used to - just
 - just like a builders ladder. Used to come in the front door and - the kitchen was here and there was no staircase or nothing, just a ladder led up to a trapdoor in the ceiling to the - to the bedroom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was this near your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh no, this was in Ashingdon. After he'd - after he'd - worked in the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of house did they live in the Jarrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh well, they lived in a - they lived in a flat in Jarrow, proper - proper flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they seem a lot worse off than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes, yes, they were worse off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there any families who were very much better off, really very posh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you describe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556  one o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 f those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. I could describe a chap called Madison and he was a jobbing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1200561\charrsid15818556 builder}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  and he li
ved in Big Bourne Road, the posh part of Jarrow like. And - he social activity was different altogether to ours, he had - piano and - he had American organ, he - daughters used to - one used to play a fiddle and another one used to play a piano }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 accordion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 . They had - that's about all I know of them, they were a different class of people altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you think that any of these groups felt superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who felt superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Oh yes, yes. Yes. Well - these people t
hat lived in Big Bourne Road. Now myself - I used to - know one of their daughter's, same age as me and - used to get on carrying on to her and talking to her and this that and the other and her father would come along and - they called this girl Minerva 
n
ow, her Christian name, and he'd see her talking to me and he would say to her, Minerva, just a minute, come on home, and take her home. And take her home, just because she was speaking to me you see. Of course I would see her the next day or the next nig
ht, I say, what's the matter with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 father? Oh, she says, he doesn't like me speaking to you. I says, what for? She says, he says you're not the same class as what we are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your family regard itself as superior to any others?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, I don
't remember anything, no. No. No, I don't remember anything like that with us, no. Just - I always thought myself superior to - to a common anyway or - you see, we used to get a lot of navies who've - come and work at glass furnaces from - straight from I
reland you see. Well I used to think myself }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 superior}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  to them. They were buck }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 navvies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  with a pick, you know, pick - digging the road up and this that and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there some families near you who you would describe as being rough and others as being respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of things did the rough people do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well the rough people - used to go out on the Saturday night and get drunk. Then the man used to come in and start knocking spots off his missus and all this that and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you know about this or just hear about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Oh no, I've seen it. I - I go in and separate the men. Aye, I go in and separate them. And I would get spots knocked off me off - off - off - off his wife. She start hitting me with the rolling pin -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Have you done this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, I've done that. I got stabbed once. Marks here yet. On the wrist here somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was in North Shields. I would be - oh - I'd be about twenty-six then. And I was in Nort
h Shields, just going down, I was on me own. I was just going down -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you think this difference between rough and respectable people is the same as craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No, there's a difference there. The craftsman - well, he's - 
he's - he's served his time to be a craftsman and he's got an ambition. Where these labourers have got no ambition. You see, they're just driftwood, they just go drifting along, they don't care. That's what I think - well, I know that. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you think it was possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
To move from one craft to another? Class? Well, no, I don't think so, I don't think so, as if you're born and brought up in the middle class you remain middle class, or you'll try to go higher up in the world - higher class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know of anybody who moved }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 upwards}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Aye, tons - tons of them. Yes, removed up - they moved up - they move up if - if they get a better job you see. See a - now a labouring man is - got a jo
b as a labourer and - when he was in this factory he - he's an intelligent sort of a chap, and he learnt how to do - the see better class people, the jobs that they were doing, he learnt the same job, you see. Now - he's seen this job as what he's seen as
 these other people doing and he's learnt it. He's seen that advertised for in another factory, you see, because the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 factory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 he was working at he was only a labourer. You see, well he's learnt }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 other job in this factory, he knows fine well that this fac
tory where he's working in wouldn't give him - a craftsman's job because he wasn't a craftsman, you see, but an - another factory what didn't know him and he's learnt this in this factory, in this other factory that didn't know him, he'd apply for the job
 and he'd get the job, you see, and therefore he stepped up and he's in the middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You know some people that did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember anyone who was described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 A particular doctor that you knew or any doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes - well - a particular doctor what I knew. I would say a particular doctor what I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why do you think he was called a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I'll tell you why he - why he was 
called a real gentleman. Now this doctor - he was - one of the young doctor's in one of these hospitals here, I think it was the Farley High, and - he got in trouble with one of the nurses, and he done something what he shouldn't have done, got her into t
rouble or something like that. And he had to get out of the hospital. Well whether he married again or not I don't know, I don't know, I don't think he did. But anyway, he come to Jarrow. And he started a practice in Jarrow in a shop. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 And he was a very, very good doctor. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Because in them days - no National Health and all that. And it was a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 enormous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  sum for the visit you see, it's ten bob for a visit or something,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  he started - you could go to him if you did - and get an interview with him and he'd give y
ou a bottle of medicine for a half a - a half a crown. Half a crown. And - I always thought he was a - a thorough gentleman. He would do anything or anyone who went there, not for just the money, if you had no half crown it didn't matter. He just treated 
- you know, and give you what he could. He was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 thorough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  gentleman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you think of the particular policeman who lived near your house when you were small, were you frightened of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I looked up to them, me, when I was a kid, I look
ed up to the policeman. We used to go and play gassy in the shop window you know, the sweet shop going looking at the window and guessing the sweets and - guessing this that and another. And the policeman used to come along and he'd - come on now, listen 
-
 give you a bat across the ear with his gloves. Well they didn't do that now you see because you could - you could prosecute them. Well me father could have prosecuted them but we - never bothered with anything like that. And I - well I - policeman - well
,
 he was policeman. He'd come and hit you across the ear with his glove, we just used to go away, we were doing wrong, standing obstructing the footpath looking in the shop window. Now I thought of that the policeman was doing his duty. But the policeman n
o
w - I don't think nothing of them at all because the policeman now, when I was younger they used to go and try all the shop doors and see if there's any burglars in, but now they just run about in their panda cars and if they see a row - they go stealing 
out of the road down a side street to miss the row altogether 'cos they're frightened. That's what I think of policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How do you think the policemen in Jarrow when you were a boy treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They treated them very fair. I thought, very fai
r. I knew a policeman in Jarrow, they called him - he was an Irishman I know, and they called him }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 Padden and - I seen them digging a trench in the street when I was a kid, digging a trench in the street with a pick and this that and another. And - one navvy would start fighting with another and a navvy down the trench here you know. And this }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 Padden come along and - says, what - what's the matter here? Here, what are you - what are you fighting about, causing an obstruction here? And - they
 would say, what are you fighting about, what's the matter with you? Or something like that. I've seen him take his tunic off and get down and get stuck in on 'em. Aye, he never locked them up. Get stuck into them, aye. And then when he was finished he'd 
come and put his tunic on like and just go on his beat. Aye. Aye, a right }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 tough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  guy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your father own the house you lived in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Just ordinary sort of a person I thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever feel that your dad had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. He had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you think about that, did you think it was a very bad thing that he had to work so hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I did. I did. I did. My fathe
r told me ha started the business with two shillings. Yes, and I quite believe him. And I says, what did you do for stock? Well, he says, you've seen corned beef tins? I says, yes. You know, the tine of corned beef? Well, he says, I went to the tip, where
 they tip them and, he says, I got three or four }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 dozen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 and he says, I brought them home, then, he says, I wrapped them all in brown paper and put them on the shelves. Wrote different things on them, nails, screws and this that and another. Put them on there
, he says, that was my stock. There you are. That was his stock. Then he says, I couldn't afford to buy a grindstone or anything for to - sharpen scissors and all this that and other but, he says, I knew how to turn them, he says, because his father had s
hown him, you see, they were cutlers you see. And, he says, he knew how to sharpen scissors but he had nothing to sharpen them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 . So he says, went to the quarries, there was some quarries in Heben and he says, I got a grindstone there, a small grindstone, he says, I paid a half a crown }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 it. Then, he says, I got a - you know, the - the mangles what they used to wash the clothes with, old days, with the big cast iron wheel. He says, I got that, and he says, I made a grind shaft out of some - any old iron
 what I found. He says, I heated it in the fire and bent it - a crankshaft. You know what a crankshaft is do you? He says, I bent that, and he says, I had wood for bearings and he said, I had the treadle, you know, made the treadle, connecting rod up to t
h
e crankshaft and - treadles like that and - made the stone to sharpen the scissors. That's how he - so you see what hard times they had. Oh yes. He says, scissors, take a long time to sharpen a pair of scissors? Oh well, I know that he says, but I sharpen
e
d them. I says, how much did you get for that? He says, he used to get sixpence a pair for them. And he says, sixpence was sixpence in them days and, he says, if I could do - six pairs of scissors, he says, it was - three bob he says, three bob was three 
bob, he says, you get a dinner for three bob for the family, you see, that was that then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What difference did it make to the family when your dad was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, well - it made a pretty big difference in them because he couldn't look after the sho
p but my older brother you see, he - he used to look after the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So he didn't lose much money by it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well he did, yes, because there's jobs what me - me brother couldn't do you see. Yes, he lost a bit money by it but of course he was very anxious for to get back onto his feet again. But I never known him really very ill. No. Only occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever need any help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When there was somebody in the district that pe
ople didn't generally like, disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed this person that they didn't like how he or she carried on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well just on one way, like they would never speak to them you see. Wouldn't speak to them, they'd just shun them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember any person who was ignored like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of things did they do that caused that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - mostly people that used to drink a lot you see. Wouldn't - you now, go in the boo
zer and - especially a woman you see. In them days - no women would go into a pub, and in them days there was no - women or young ladies wore lipstick nor nothing like that. You see, if they had lipstick and they seen a woman at the public house well they
 were put down as prostitutes, you see, and people wouldna speak to them, and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Did you ever hear of anything called rough music, people going outside a house and banging on kettles and things, shouting to try and force somebody to leave the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I've never known of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you given lessons by either of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, well - as I told you before - my mother died when I was three months old and I growed up by me father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he ever give you lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever have a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I'd be five as far as I know. Five years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you first started school what time in the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
I went to school at nine o'clock in the morning. Then - at twelve o'clock I used to come home for me dinner. Then I used to go back to school again at one o'clock. Then I was finished at four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you go all day right
 from the beginning, you didn't start only mornings and then later on go in the afternoon, you went all day from the age of five did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Nine. And then I come here - home for me dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 But you went back in the afternoon even when you were five did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of school was it, was it a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was a Church school, it was a Church of England school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was it a day school, there weren't any boarders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Day school, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was it boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Boys and girls, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Boys and girls in the same classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you divided, boys one side of the room and girls the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's - so, that's so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 On shank's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 pony}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , me feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did it take you to walk there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Just about ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Myself. Just on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You had your midday meal at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I had me midday meal at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well I didn't like school and I'll tell you the reason why. Because me father was a busy man, he's looking after the business you see and - I used to more or less get myself ready for school you see, well - I generally used to be late and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 wasn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 in a hurry for to go to school. I - I used to go and look in the bins of other shops, you know, they had their bins out and they used to put old boot laces in and all this that and other and empty cigarette packets, and I used to go look for cigarette ca
rds, and that used to make us late for school. Then when I went to school late - I used to get the stick, the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You weren't very keen on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I wasn't very keen on it, but still I wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 frightened}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , I wasn't frightened of the cane or nothing, I just expected it and that was that, I just hold me hand out and just got it and that was that..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I liked the teachers very well, they were - they were ladies - teacher. They weren't men, they were lad
ies. Yes, yes, I liked the teachers all right, never had any trouble with the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they say that some things were very important in life, did the teachers pick out certain things as being very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - yes. They used to tell yo
u with a Church of England school they used to tell you to always tell the truth and don't tell any lies. And - always obey your parents. I remember all that. And I - I think that was about all like in that light.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 If you did something the teachers didn't like, like going to school late, you got the stick or was it the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was a cane. Cane - hold your hand out. Cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they have any other ways of disapproving, when you did anything wrong in the classroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, if you done somet
hing wrong and - the teacher - my teacher, a very good teacher, and - she - maybe she give me about our strokes with the cane and - never used to have any effect on me, I didn't care. And - 'cos I didn't start to cry or something like that. She says, you 
don't seem to take any effect with the cane, she says, I'll send you to the master. The master. Well the master, he was paralysed in one arm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 
And I would rather be sent to the master than be caned by teacher because he couldn't hurt you at all. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Then of cour
se I used to be the same with the master, 'cos I - the master, he seen that it had no effect so - he would send us to his wife which was the mistress. Now the mistress, used to say, bend down. And of course I wouldn't bed down, so she would get a hold of 
m
e, I was just a kid, she'd get a hold of me and she'd put me over her knee and get the cane out. Well into me behind with the cane you see, 'til I started to shout and then she says, that'll make you be a good lad and all this that and other and that was 
that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they used to cane the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of things did you have to do in that school to be caned, apart from being late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - if you - took any sweets to school. And they caught you eating them 
or anything you used to get the cane for that. And I think I've told you that I used to get a ha'penny every morning off me father - for sweets. And of course I was often brought out you see for - then they used to take the sweets off me. And she used to 
put them in the desk. And - she would give you them when you went home. And often - when she put my sweets in the desk someone used to steal them. I've told you that, aye. That's right, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Anything else that meant that you got the cane at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 
Yes, you got the - you got the cane if she caught you copying from someone, you see, you're doing a sum and you weren't sure, you'd look and see what someone else was doing and if she caught you, you got the cane for that.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your father show an interest, was he interested in what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No he's too interested in the business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he never even ask you what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 go to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did the other children at this school come from the same kind of homes as you or different kind of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well all come from different kind of homes, there was - some come from pretty high class homes and some from pretty low class homes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did the teachers used to pick out some children for special treatment, favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, they were all the same. My teacher - they're all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of gangs or groups were there in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Well - we all used to play toget
her, the girls and the boys in the playground, all played together, and - the only trouble we ever had was - on St Patrick\rquote 
s Day, the Catholics used to come round to our school, E.I.L.S. you know, and - of course there used to be - we - they used to have paper balls you know, with string round them you know and - E.I.L.S., and it started you know.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What does E.I.L.S. stand for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 English, Irish or Scotch. E.I.L.S. you see. And of course we were English you know and, were taking English and they woul
d get - would try and get stuck into you with these paper balls and hit you and this that and other and there used to be proper rows on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That was the only gangs you can remember and that was just once a year was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That was once a year - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 These were kids from other schools?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, the kids from the - from the Catholic schools, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember any children in your school who were always left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. I can't but - of course in the school I can remember 
- some boys and girls - they were - a quiet nature you see. And - when they come to school they would just stand up aside the wall in the playground you see and - never play games or nothing you see. Now if that happened and I seen any of them myself I us
e
d to go up and ask them what was the matter you see, and, come on and play, skipping ropes or used to play marbles and we used to have tops and - and especially the boys I would - you know, give them my top and show them how to - play top and this that an
d other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you go on to another school after this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 If you had had the chance would you have stayed longer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. I'll tell you the reason why, I wanted to go to work and earn some money to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any part time education after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Have you got any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes. Tons. Yes, tons of regrets, tons of regrets. Well - more or less I - as I told you before
 - for to go and serve me time - had to serve me time to be an engineer you see. Well if I'd have had a better }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 education}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 I would be getting farther up the ladder in engineering you see, I would have been the chief engineer or something like that you see. Well I hadn't the education. And of course that handicapped me a lot that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you think you benefitted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. But - I've learnt more since I left school than what I learnt when I was at school. Yes yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I've already asked you about your part time jobs haven't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you get your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me first full time job? When I left school when I was fourteen - I went into a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 chemist\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How was that arranged, did you just go to the shop or did you know somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I knew a girl what worked - worked in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 baker\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  shop and I've told you about me working in the baker's shop. Well this girl in the baker's shop - she - knew this chemist. And - she says, to me, I th
ink it would be quite a good job for you if you - went to this chemist, you see. So I went to the chemist and - had a talk to him like and he says, oh yes, he says - I can give you a job. And, he says, running the errands and this that and the other and, 
h
e says, when you get older, he says, you can be the assistant in the chemist shop you know. Now that was a pretty decent job. Because the chemist was a decent sort of a chap and - when the chemists shop was shut he used to go out and he used to do this - 
show slides and that in a temperance hall of - you know, lantern slides. Well I was interested in that and he taught me with him and - I learned all that, how to show these slides, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember what year that was, was that 1907?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, it would be 1907.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you start straight after you left school in the summer was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I left school when I was - no, I left when I was fourteen, me birthday. July.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you first started you were doing errands, taking things to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Ye
s, taking things to people, just - just running errands and - there wasn't a great lot of errands to do, I used to serve customers and all this that and other as well you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What hours did you work on weekdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I used to start about nine o'clock in the morning and - we used to finish about seven or eight o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of break did you have in the middle of the days, anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, yes, I had a break but - I never went home. No, I just - used to - me father used to put 
me some sandwiches up or something like that, I used to have them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you were there for nearly eleven hours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you work Saturday or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We worked Saturday but not Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The same hours on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Same hours on Saturday, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you get a half day or did you do six full days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
You got a half day on a Wednesday, but the half day on a Wednesday - I used to go with the chemist to some temperance hall and show these slides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you get any holiday with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much were you paid when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Be about four and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much did you give to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me father would never take nothing from me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So that was all pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So what did you spend your money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I was a great man for - great boy for photography. And I bought a camera and - it used to take all me pocket money buyin
g - the films, they weren't films then, they were slides or glass. Plates they used to call them, glass plates. Well I used to spend all me money on that photography, taking people's photo's and all this that and other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you get on with the people that you worked with, was there only just the chemist in the shop or were there other people there?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 There was the just the chemist himself and he was a very decent sort of a chap and I got on very well with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Liked it, yes, I liked the work very much, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did you do this job for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 From the age of fourteen up to sixteen. Yes, when I was sixteen I - always had a ambition for to be an engineer. And - I says to me f
ather, I'm going to leave the chemist and I'd like to serve me time to be an engineer. So me father says - I'm afraid that you'll never be able to serve your time to be an engineer? So I says, why? Well, he says, with your father having a shop in business
,
 he says, they won't let anyone serve their time. That was in Palmers of Jarrow, if their father's in business. So I says, why? Well, he says, there's a Mr - Madison and, he says, he's the foreman engineer at Palmers and, he says, if you don't go to his c
h
urch - which was a - Wesleyan chapel like - he says, you can't get started, you see. So I says, I'll go and see him. You see. So I went to see him. So the first thing he asks is what church I went to you see. So I says, I go to the Christchurch. Aye, Chur
ch - Church of England, used to call in the Christchurch in Jarrow, the Church of England, I said, I go to Church of England. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 
So he says, well if you had have gone to the Wesleyan chapel, he says, I could have give you a job, but - he says, with you going to the Church of England, he says, we're not starting anyone from the Church of England. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I said, that's all right. Come and told me father so me father says, what? He says, why not come and work for me in the ironmongers shop you - see. So I says, no, I say
s, I want to serve me time to be an engineer you see. So - that night - I got some pen and paper and envelopes and I wrote to different firms you see. I wrote to the - I wrote letters to different engineering firms and I got a reply from - Parsons Marine 
S
team Turbine Company at Wallsend. So I went to interview the manager there and - he says that they were mostly premium apprentices there but, he says, we have some that's - that's not premium apprentices and if you couldn't pay a premium, but, he says, go
 
and have a talk to your father, see if your father can afford to pay premium you see and let me know you see. So I see me father and me father says, certainly not, he says, I couldn't pay any premium, he says, just - people like - Dodds the butcher, he sa
y
s, and you know, people with plenty of money, he says, he says, I couldn't pay any premium. So I went and told the manager that and he says, quite all right. He says, but - now the premium apprentices here, he says - they - not particular when they come t
o
 work and they're not particular when they go home, they can go home when they like you see, but you - you'll have fixed hours. You'll have to start at six o'clock in the morning and finish at five o'clock at night you see. I says, quite all right. So I g
ot started and - I had to get up at four o'clock in the morning and get the ferry over the river to - Howden, travel from Howden to Wallsend in the tramcar to work and I had to be there six o'clock in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was a long day for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh - you're telling me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You were an apprentice engineer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of engineer were you exactly, what were you learning, what kind of engineering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I was learning - lathe work and all kinds of engineering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 All to do with shipbuilding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 condensers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  in shops you see, boilers in ships and - the main engines in ships, learning to make them, run them then after you'd - when I'd got - a bit older I would be like the leading lad on - mending to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 condensers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  for ships you see
 and younger apprentices I used to show them how to go on and all this that and other. Now when I got older - if they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 were putting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  engines in a ship, they mostly were ships, putting engines in the ship at maybe - the Naval yard that does - Elsig - it was E
lsig then. Well - I used to go there on a cruiser and I would - I would have and engine under - three engine rooms and there'd be the port engine room, centre engine room and starboard engine room, now I would take charge of an engine room and put the tur
bines in you see, with - more lads you see and also men, you see. Now when the ship was finished I used to run the trials on the ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 This is still whilst you're an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, still only an apprentice, run the trails on the ship. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 And - 
this ship I remember pretty well was called the H.M.S. Weymouth, that was a cruiser. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Now we done all the trials on her and of course, with me just being a young lad, an apprentice and all this that and other, of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 course}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  the whole crew was on you know, the s
ailors. And the Naval engineer was on and we were showing them how the - the engines worked and all this that and other, and - we used to do thirty-six hours full speed trials and all the trials, well I remember - on this ship - used to sleep in a hammock
 
you see. Well I was that tired - I slung me hammock up, there was hooks you know, up on - in - on the deck, sling me hammock up and I put mine up underneath a gun, which I didn't know, the gun was there you see. And, this gun is a six inch gun and I didn'
t
 know. Well, while I was asleep, this is during the day, when I was asleep, they started to do the Navy started their gun trials you see. And of course as soon as they fired the gun the concussion of the gun snapped the bolt on my hammock you see, and of 
course I'm just down on the bottom. Then of course after that I - I learnt you see, put it out of the road of the guns.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you were taking part in these trials, was this soon after you were sixteen or were you nearer twenty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh - it was - I'd be about - seventeen or eighteen. Seventeen or eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you worked six o'clock in the morning 'til five in the afternoon five days a week or six days a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Used to work from six o'clock in the morning 'til five o'clock at night and we had
 a half day off on a Saturday, used to finish at twelve o'clock on a Saturday. No Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was six and a half days then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of break did you have during this eleven hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Used to have - a break at nine o'clock for your breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Half an hour. Then dinner time you had from twelve 'til one - one hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have a break in the afternoons or for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You worked straight through from one o'clock 'til five did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's right, yes, no break.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 you get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No fear. Holiday was a torture. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well cos you had no money. You couldn't have a holiday, you had - no money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We got - when I started I got four and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The same as you got in the shop?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Same as I got at the chemists, four and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did it stay the same right through your apprenticeship, was it a seven year apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Five. Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you getting four and six all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh no, you got a rise of a shilling a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you were getting nine and six by the time you'd finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Aye, about nine and six and - when we were finished then they would - give you - 
your out your time they'd give you thirty shilling a week. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
You'd have nine and six just before you finished your apprenticeship and then when you started afterwards you went right up to thirty shillings a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, you're our your time yo
u see, you're out your time when you're twenty-one you're out your time you see and your a full fledged engineer you see. And - I think it was thirty shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you think about your wage as an apprentice, were you satisfied with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you think it was unfair then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Yes. For the work you done it was very unfair, you done the same work as a man. You see, you done the same work as a man and sometimes you done more work than a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 do you think you ought to have got when you were seventeen or eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I - we thought - I thought we should get - as much as the men. You see, because we done the same work as the men. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 You see, there'd be a man working a lathe here, I'd be working a lathe just next to him doing the same job. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
You see. And of course they had a union you see, apprentices had no union. And of course they got the money }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 the union you see, we had no union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you start to give money to your father as you were getting more or did you always keep all your money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No I - when I got more money - I used to give it to me father and me father generally used to give us half on it back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you still spending it on slides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I was still spending it on photography and this that and other, yes. And smoking, and smoking. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you get on with your workmates, the other apprentices and the men you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, I got on with the - the ones me own class very well. But these premium apprentices, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 These were the ones that were posher than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's right, the - the posh lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of backgrounds did they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well their - lived in Witney Bay and Monksheaton and all them places, posh lads you know and could start
 when they liked and - this that and other. And they used to try and take a rise - they had a better education than us and they used to try and take a rise out of us people that - well, me, I used to detest them. Because they would get a lad and - what wa
s
n't very well - there's lads like that wasn't very witty you know, and they used to go to him and - they George, come here. 'Course the lad would go up. Say, go to stores and get me a long stand. You see. So the lad never knew, he got to store and ask the
 
storekeeper for a long stand. Of course the storekeepers knew someone was having them on, they just let them stand there you see. And - after he stood there about a couple of hours or something - chargeman used to come along and say, they what are you doi
n
g here, what's the matter you're not on your job? Oh, he says, so and so sent us for a long stand. Well, he says, you've stood long enough haven't you, get on with that job. Now I used to resent all that. Aye. Now I remember one of the - and it was - you 
know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Dodd\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 the butcher in Newcastle, well it was one of his sons, premium apprentice. And - just when buzzer was blowing or going to blow for five o'clock and all made a dish for the gate this lad, Dodd's son he got a - a chain sling and put it through one
 of the apprentice lad's coat, right through his arms you know, a chain sling and put the shackle on and put it on the big crane and hoisted it right up to the top of the shop, just when the lad had to go home you see. And so I see them doing it, but he h
a
d getting it up to the top of the shop when I see them doing it and I - I asked them, I said, what's - what's the idea of that? Oh, he said, just a bit of fun. I said, that's no fun, I said, the lad's got to go home, I said, he's got to catch the ferry an
d
 all, that's no fun. So he says to me, you might not think it is, but, he says, I think it is. A well, I said, it's coming down - and I pulled the handle of the crane so none'd no so he'd leave it alone. And - I - I told him to leave it alone and - them -
 
then he turned round to me and - he asked me what was the matter with me, you see, so - I says, well you're not going to - a young lad like that I said, just started working, I said, trying to play a prank on him, I said, you're not going to do it. So he 
s
ays, well, what've you got to do with it, I'll punch your nose. So I says, get yourself started. And so - made a punch at me and of course - we had a bit of a fight and in the finish I knocked him down. And - that was that. That finished that subject alto
gether.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you didn't get any more trouble with these premium apprentices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no, no, never had any more trouble with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you get on well with them after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, just ignores them that was all. Different class of people altogether you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 But you got on all right with the other apprentices did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The other apprentices? Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And the other men who worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, that's true, that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about your employer in the shipyard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well it wasn't a shipyard, an engineering works you see, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 get on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well the foreman, he was all right, but the manager - he had his favourites and he wasn't all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of people were his favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well - his favourites was more premium apprentices, see, better class apprentices and - as I told you I used to go away on different jobs, fitting turbines in cruisers and this that and other. Well the last job I was on was at - Elsig shipyard, Vickers Ar
m
strong. And it was a ship called the Weymouth, and - we finished it, went trails on it and everything, finished it and - the outside foreman on that job, he said, the next job for you will be at Dumbarton, he says, there's two destroyers to do there, torp
e
do destroyers, one called the Beaver and one called the Rajah. Just go home and call in at Wallsand works and see Mr Ford, that was the manager, and tell him that you're going to Dumbarton, he said. Right. So I went along to see Mr Ford and told him that 
- I was going to Dumbarton the following week. Or two destroyers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 torpedo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 destroyers. So he says, I'm afraid you're not. I says, how's that? He says, I want you in the shop. I want you back in the factory, he says, because - Mr Wilson in the tool room, he sa
ys, his son is going, you see. Well - you couldn't do nothing you see, you just had to go back in the shop and that was that. That's the kind of thing the manager did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the owners or the board of directors, did you ever come across them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. Just the manager, you never come across the board of directors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the work you were doing while you were an apprentice, how did you feel about the actual work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, I felt - the work was all right, I was quite satisfied wit
h the work. But - I wasn't satisfied with the pay because you were doing - when you got on apprentice you know and you were about seventeen or eighteen you could do as much work as a man. And there's a man working the next machine to you getting full pay 
a
nd you were doing the same job as him and just getting about four and six you see. No, that - that didn't seem right. And of course he had a trade union, apprentices had no trade union, you couldn't do nothing about it. If you weren't satisfied well - you
 get out, and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You served your time there and then you carried on in the same line did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For how long, did you stay in the same line of business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I stayed in the same line of business - now let me see, yes, I
 stayed in the same line of business then there was a big depression. And - I went and got a job as maintenance engineer for the British Oxygen Company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you get laid off the ship you were on, when you were an apprentice you were based at the works weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you're apprentice, no. No. When you're apprentice - now what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 After you were finished didn't you work on ships most of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Aye, oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For the first few years when you were an apprentice you were in Wallsend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Now - that's right, apprentice at Wallsend. Now I didn't finish me time at Parsons Marine Turbine Company. Now this is a funny thing, I've just remembered it. Sir Charles Parson, that was the owner of the - the place I - I neve
r come across him like - but - when aeroplanes first start flying about - Sir Charles Parsons, there was going to be some aeroplanes on Newcastle Town Moor, you see, and we had never seen one, the lads had never seen one. And Sir Charles Parsons was going
 
to be there. So of course, me being one of the older apprentices in Parsons, they come to me and said they would like to go and see these aeroplanes you see. Well, I says, that's up to you, I says, if you want to go, I says, you'll have to take a day off 
f
or to go you see. So they had a meeting among theirselves - and - they decided for to take the next day off for to go and see the aeroplanes you see. So of course there's a lot of - toots in an engineering works, and someone told Ford the manager that the
 
lads was going to be off you see. They're going on the - on the next - the Wednesday, the next day. So he sent for me, me being the oldest apprentice. And he says to me he says, in that right that the - the apprentices is going to take a day off tomorrow 
f
or to go and and see the aeroplanes? I says, yes, that's so. Sell, he says, you might go and tell them that anyone at takes a day off tomorrow - they'll be finished - sacked. Right. So I went and told them. So they says, that didn't matter, we're going to
 have a day off whether we get sacked or whether we don't get sacked. See? Right. So they took the day off. Now after we had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 a day}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  off and were coming in the following morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have the day off as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. The following morning when we come in - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 our}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 check was stopped, used to get a check then when you started, your brass check you know your number on. Well when I went in there was - oh there'd be about - five or six lads standing there. I says, what's the matter. They says, our chec
ks are stopped, we're sacked. And so I went down and of course my check was stopped and all - sacked. So - this was six o'clock in the morning. So waited 'til ford the manager come in at nine o'clock, he come in at nine o'clock, with - the Daily - Mirror 
o
r something under his arm, walking down the street. So I stopped him in the street and asked him what was the matter. He said, I told you what was the matter. He said, you're finished, he said, the whole lot of you, finished. And - I said, what about the 
premium apprentices, you see. Oh well, he says, that's all right for them, he says, we can't finish them, they've paid for to work here. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Youse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  chaps don't, he said, you're all finished. And he says, another thing I'll tell you, he says, I've phoned - he sai
d, you understand the Master's Federation don't you? I says, yes. Well, he says, I've give - details to the Master's Federation and, he says, we've stopped you from getting a job at any other engineering factory. I says, very good. You see, so - lad, me s
a
ys very good. So I got a hold of one of the lads we - a mate of mine and we went to the North Eastern Marine. Asked them if they wanted any improvers you see. In Mitherton Line you see. So they says, where did you work last? You see. Parsons Marine. Oh - 
h
e goes into his office and he comes back, he got on the phone and he comes back again, no, he says, can't start you. He says, you're stopped, all over the river, he said, you wont get a job. And I says, that means we're - we'll not be able to finish our t
i
me as - after working all this time, won't be able to finish our time as engineers. Well, he says, it looks like it, he says, it's - it's wrong, I know that but, he says, your manager has done it and that was that. So I went from there to Wallsend Slipway
 and asked them. Same thing happened there. I went from there to a shipyard called Clements. And - the foreman there, he seemed to be a sort of a funny sort of a chap, and he says, where did you work last? You see. So I said, Parsons Marine Steam }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Turbine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  Wo
rks. So he said, what do they make there? So I says, Turbines. So he says, what - what bines? You know, trying to be funny, I said, no turbines, you never heard of them? But anyway he said, no, he says - well I'm not starting anyone, he says, we've had wo
r
d from your manager and - he says, we - we can't - we can't start you. So of course I come home, told me father and - me father said, it's hard lines and you'll just have to come and stop here with me you see, work in the shop you see. So - about two days
 
after that I seen a job in the paper for - engineer improver wanted. And this was Taylor and Palestine, Dunston. So I goes there. And I seen the owner of the factory, a chap called Mr Taylor. And he was very nice chap. Asked me where I worked and why I wa
s finished and I told him. And he says, it's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 ridiculous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , that's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 ridiculous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
. So I says, that's what I thought. But, I says, it seems to be the master's federation and all this business and - nobody has got to start us. Oh well, he says, I'll start you. When 
can you start, you see. Had a good talk to him in his home, took us home to talk to him. And I told him, start any time. So he says, it's a long travel }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  Jarrow to Dunson, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Whereabouts is Dunston?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Dunston - it's - outside of Gateshea
d. You - do you know where - you've heard of Dunston Power Station I daresay, yes, it's out - a long travel. So I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 told me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 father like, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 I said}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 I've been and got a job at Taylor and Palaces at Dunston. And - he says, that's a long way to travel, it'll cost y
ou your wages for train fare you see. So I says, I'll try and get a lodge there, you see. So anyway I went in to see Mr Taylor about it and asked him if he knew of anyone you see, what took boarders in you see. So he says, I don't know of anyone but, he s
a
ys, I'll make enquiries. So he made enquires and he come and told me that there was a lady in a certain street and - she would take us in you see. And - I went to see her and - she says she would take me in for ten shilling a week. You see, well that was 
quite all right so I went and lodged there and - and I finished me time there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old were you when you started }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 working at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  Dunston?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I'd be about - nineteen. And I finished me time when I was twenty-one. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 
Now when I - I got on very well at Taylor\rquote 
s - Taylor Pilaster and - the jobs you used to have to do there, the ships come in are mostly Austrian ships and - I used to - be a job abroad - maybe is the big end wanted - re-metalling or something like that you know, the big end of the ships, a big th
ing about sixteen inches diameter and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well I used to get a sculler boat, belonged to Taylor Pallister like, and just one - one car at the back and rowed to the big ship and see what wanted }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 doing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , and I used to take the bearing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , put it in this scul
ler boat, scull it back to the works and re-metal it, then put it in a lathe, bore it out to size, chip all the oilways in it, take it back to the ship and fit it up for them and everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 This would be during the war wouldn't it, about 1916 or so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was - oh it was - half a minute a now it would - during the war - it was before the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You started work in 1911 when you were fourteen didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I'm seventy-seven now. Yes, oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you were fourteen in 1911, so in 1916, that's when you were nineteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's right, near about the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I wondered how there were Austrian ships because they were fighting on Germany's side weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Ah well, the war wasn't on then was it. Mostly - I know they were Austrian ships there. Well, there might have been an Austrian Shipment - some British ships but - But I - I can remember going aboard an Austrian ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 From 1916 how long did you work at Dunston?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I worked at Dunston 'til I was - twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Then you finished your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And then you went where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now I finished me time and - I went and seen Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 Taylor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , Mr Taylor was quite highly satisfied with my work and I went to see him and told him I would like to go to sea. Well he was a seagoing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4858824\charrsid15818556 engineer
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , he had his chief's ticket you know, Mr Taylor. And he says, you would like to go to sea. Well, he says, I'll get you a shop. But, he says, I'll get you a good ship an
d, he says, you'll learn more on this ship than, he says, what you'll learn in here. With your trade. And he says, it'll be an old ship. Well, I says, I'm quite satisfied with any sort of a ship. So he got us a ship. And this ship was - they called it the
 
Huncliffe - steamship Huncliffe. And - it was twenty-one year old. And - everything - everything was the matter with it. You were - you were working, you night and day an board this hip you know, the packet used to blow out of the pistons and - the feed p
ump wouldn't pump water in the boiler and all this that and other and - I learnt quite - quite a lot with that ship. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
hat ship I done - I done - seven month in it and - when it came back I had enough - seven month of that ship I left. And I got another ship, a newer ship.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was your job on this first ship, what were you called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I was - third engineer. Third engineer. Carrying three engineers. Chief, second then myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Then you went on to another ship, what were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I was fourth engineer on a bigger ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long were you on this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I just done one voyage on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I done one voyage on there. Then I believe the first world war broke out. That was that. I done one voyage on that and I come bac
k and the first world war broke out and I went into Palmers in Jarrow. As - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 maintenance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 fitter. And while I was in there the war broke out, that was right. The zeppelins come down and bombed Palmers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 while}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 I was in it, that's right. And - when the war was over - we all got the sack. You know, things was bad, they all finished. Then I got a job at the British Oxygen Company in Shields Road and - I worked there for quite a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I worked there for about - oh - about ten year, ten or twelve year at the British Oxygen Company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was your position there, what were you called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Same, maintenance engineer - maintenance engineer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember how old you were when you left that job or what year it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I couldn't tell you how old I was but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was it before the second world war started?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. Yes. It was before the second world war started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Before the Jarrow march?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did you go from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I went from there to - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 George}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  Angus, the oil seal people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The same. Well I was foreman there at George Angus's. And - they were making these }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 fluid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  seals you know, you know what they are for motor cars this that and 
other. And - I didn't work a great length of time there - because the second world war broke out. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you mean just a couple of years or less than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well it might have been - it wouldn't be a couple of years I don't think, no. Maybe abo
ut - eight or nine month. And - there was a friend of mine, what I often used to do odd jobs for, now he was a - he had - had a welding - well he was managing director of a welding business, what they call Welders Limited. And - he asked me, he come and a
sked me if I would start for him. Because they were - you know, when these magnetic }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 mines}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 what the Germans had out you see, well of course these magnetic mines, they were - steel ship used to attract them you see, they were floating about, used to attract t
hem and they come in contact with the ship and they blow the ship up. So someone invented what they called degauzing the ships. Well Welders Limited had the job for to degauze these ships and - he wanted me for to take these - electric welding plants wher
e they were doing these ships you see and run the electric welding plant while the welders was putting this degauzing business on them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556 
I worked there 'til - yes, I worked there 'til the war was over.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now - while the war was on
 - for Welders Limited. They were building the Mulberry harbour for the invasion, you see. You would read about that, like they had no place for to - for to land or nothing and - of course the brains department they decided to make their own harbour you s
e
e. So - Welders Limited, they had the job of - making this Mulberry harbour. Well I had to go to Colchester, it was a restricted area, just in a small place called Wivenhoe in - in Colchester, Well that's where the shipyard is, small shipyard. Well - we m
a
de the Mulberry harbour there and of course I was looking after - about - seven or eight petrol electric welding plants you see, welding this Mulberry harbour. And - when the Mulberry harbour was finished and - it was going to get towed over to Normandy a
nd I got instructions, I had to stop there - 'til it was towed over Normandy and I had to still stop there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 With the harbour or in Colchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In Colchester, I was still stop there to see if the invasion was a success. If it wasn't a success I h
ad to go over to Normandy with the machines and repair it if the Germans, you know, bashed it about, you see, to go over there and repair. But anyway, D Day come and the invasion come off and everything was all right so - I come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So what was your next job after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
After the war. Oh I was all over the place after the war - let me think. Well that was that. The next job was Palmer Trade a research station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's - in Wallsdend. It's a- hey call it the - the British - Ship Research Station now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was your job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me job there was the same, maintenance fitter there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 
Now - what I used to do there - I used to - they used to get gear - what they called spherical gear, that's turbine gear for - you know that doesn't run direct, it runs onto a gear and geared down you see for the driver for power. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - my job was there - for to run these turbines and run these gears for - a hundred hours, you see, and - after I run them a hundred hours used to take the
 covers off and examine them and see what wear and tear we had and all this that and another and - that was that. I finished - I retired from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you were there for quite a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh I was there - yes, oh yes, quite a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you retire in 1960?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I retired when I was - sixty - sixty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Would you rather have had a completely different kind of job than being a maintenance engineer and a seagoing engineer if you'd been able to choose?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, my ambition was for to be - an engineer and a seagoing engineer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you achieved it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes, seagoing engineer, but I hadn't the education. When I was younger. My home life, I had no mother and that and - I hadn't the education for to - sit for me exams}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9054837\charrsid15818556  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 to be chief engineer you see. And I hadn't the money to join the Freemasons and - so my ship is no longer. If I had me life to go over again I would - sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 But you would rather have been a chief engineer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Chief engineer, aye, that's right, chief engineer. Th
at was my ambition, to be a chief engineer but of course - never had the education, impossible to get a education }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 you see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 .

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you belong to any trade unions after you'd served your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes. Amalgamated Engineering union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you take part in any union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. I detested unions. But I had to be in them for to get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you think that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well the employer - the employer - he wants you to do as much as you can for very little payment. And I found that out in all these big factories. But in a smaller factory where it's a - one man owns it, you get a fair crack of the whip there and
 you get paid for what you can do, if you - do a job and he makes a good profit in it, he'll give you a - a fair wage. Bug in the big factories, no, you're just a number.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Interest? In - in what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Before 1919 some people say there was a great division between craftsmen on the one hard and other workers did you think there were any big gaps?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes, there's a big gap there, well there's - there's 
craftsmen and labourers you see. Well there's a big difference there because - now - myself I'm sorry for a labourer because a labourer - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 minority}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  of them, they couldn't afford for to go and serve their time you see, their parents were poor and all this that and the other and they couldn't afford to go and serve their time you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 And - then of course you come across some labourers that knows more than you, or think they know more than you, you see, they see you doing a job you see and - oh - any damn bugger can do that you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You come across labourers like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
You also mentioned differences between the apprentices, when you got older were there premium apprentices working on the same kind of jobs as you, did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 still find}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  this difference, lads that had been with you at Palmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
No. No. No. No, well that's - that's queer you asking that. There was a - a premium apprentice, they called him Askalon, I don't know whether it's a Norwegian name or what it is, but - yes, it sounds like it, but 
anyway, he was a premium apprentice. He's a canny enough lad. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 
I never seen him anyone - for years and years 'til while I was working for the British Oxygen Company, Swann and Hunters, they wanted to use these oil acetylene, well the British Oxygen used to make that, that's acetylene gas in a bottle you see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
This of course is dissolved in acid too so it won't explode and all the rest of it, I don't suppose you know anything about that, but anyway - I had to go to Swann and Hunters to see about it, to see if 
it was suitable for to put in you see. And I had to see the head engineer. And when I went into the head }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 engineer\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 office, who do you think it was. That's right. And - the people that made this - these old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 acetylene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
, they called them Allen Liversedge and 
of course they were amalgamated with the British Oxygen. Well I had to go there and see this chap and of course he knew us straight away and he says, Allen Liversedge, he says, are you partner in the company, you see. 'Cos they called me Allen you see. I 
s
ays, I'm very sorry, I says, I'm not partner in the company, I wish I was. So he says, a lot of years since I've seen you. I says oh yes, that's so. Now there was a difference. He was head engineer of a big place like Swann and Hunter. Me, I was just ordi
nary - maintenance fitter you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you think that was general among premium apprentices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They got the top jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's right. That's right. They got the jobs - top jobs. They had influence. Well and education, I don't know, som
e of them had a lot of education but I don't think on the engineering side you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Full time work? No. No. No, no, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you continue to live at home when you started work in the chemists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When I started work in the chemist shop I was still at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When you started serving your time you were at home, did you stay at home all the time until you went to Dunston?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 True. All the time, I started at Dunston then I lodged at Dunston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 At Dunston you'd done about four years of your time when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's be all, yes. About three or four year, that would be all, first and then I went to sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For about the first six years after you left school you were living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's true, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did starting full time work change your relationship with hour father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He just treat - just the same way, he treat me the same way and I treat him the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - just the same - just - all the same, just treat the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you spend Sundays any different after you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, just the same. Just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I used to go to Sunday school when I was younger but when I started to work, no. I used to go to church then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you take any interest in politics when you started work at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 What}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  kind of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well just that - I was always a Conservative, me father was a Conservative. And I was always a Conservative and I still }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 am}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  a Conservative. That was the only interest I took in then, I never vote anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What's your reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 Well when I was working - we all
 work for our living, we're all labour men, work by the sweat of our brow and when I was working, I was working on a bench and the piece clerk come up to me and - says, how much will you do that job for bob? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So - I told him what I would do it for. He says,
 right, very good. He goes to the chap on the next bench and the same union as me, same society as me, goes and asks him, how much will you do this job for George? So he turns round and he says, how much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  Bob Allen doing it for? That was me. So he told h
im. He says, I'll do it for a half a crown cheaper than him. See, so that finished me with Labour. Never voted Labour after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 After you'd started work did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way as before or did you do any different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well I think - when I started work I had no time for to do any different things. Before I started work I used to have hobbies - taking - photography. You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 see,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  when started work I - hadn't the time to do that, I had to give that up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you go out in the evenings after you'd started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of places did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well mostly we'd go to the theatre or - pictures or something like that mostly, that didn't - I used to do a lot of fishing. Fishing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who did you go with when you went to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I generally went with my young lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old were you when you started courting then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Be about twenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have just this one young lady all the time or did you used to make new fr
iends in this period as a young man before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well yes - yes - I - had - more or less three or four young ladies you know, picked the best one. That's right. I know there was a lot of that and I can't understand it - with a young chap l
ike yourself like and they get a hold of one girl and - you - you get married. There's a lot of that done - -now, now I don't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 believe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 Yes, I - I didn't believe in that, have one young lady, take her out, very nice and all this that and what - but - I
 found out that I don't think she'll be suitable for me so I used to I give her the run light and get a hold of another one and - see what she was like and - you find }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556  lot of things like that - maybe as you found her father was a drunkard or her mother was a drunkard or something you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember how you used to meet your new friends, girl friends for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How I used to meet them? Yes, my - my missus - well I met her - I met her - in Jarrow railway station and she was going to Glasg
ow and she was a jolly - very jolly sort of a girl and - when the guard used to come for to put his little green light for let the engine driver see it she would go and steal his lamp and hide it somewhere and he's looking all over the place for that and 
I
 thought that was very amusing. And then I got on talking to her and I got to know she was a - in - a general servant in Wales what they called it then, you know somewhere in Perthshire. So I got going out with her and she was very nice girl and we got ma
rried and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever bring your friends }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 home}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  in the years before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Your father was interested was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, that's all - quite all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he expect to be told where you were going when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, didn't enquire about that. You could stop out all night, he'd never say anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You were twenty-one when you married were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I was over twenty-one, twenty-two. Between twenty-two or twenty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long had you known your wife then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Quite - a couple of year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well she was born in Birmingham. In Birmingham, yes, and - work was bad to get or her father and brothers and this that and other and they come to Jarrow a
nd - they were - they used to work in a tube works in Birmingham. Well the tube works closes down or something and there was a tube works in Jarrow. They come from Birmingham to Jarrow and they got a job at the tube works and that was that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you save up any money before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your father help you with setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Help us in what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Engaged about twelve month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you tell me something about hour wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The wedding, yes. I was married in the oldest church in - well I think it's the oldest church in England, at St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 Bede's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  church in Jarrow, I expect you'll know about it. Yes, I was married in St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 Bede\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  church at Jarrow and - I enga
ged a hall for the reception. I did - I had no honeymoon because the war was on and - I had to tell a few lies for to get off to get married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you pay for everything, or did her family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I paid for everything. I paid for everything. There 
weren't very - you know, in the same position as what I was. The wife's father he was just a labouring man and they were hard times then. Her mother used to take a lot of washing in for to help the - family income. And - of course she used to have to go o
ut to work you see and - I raised all the wedding myself and I paid for everything myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you get many presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, a good few presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of things, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes - electric - toasters and electric kettle and ornaments and - and the missus - sheets and blankets }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  the bottom drawer and all this that and the other, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How many guests were there at the wedding?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 There'd be quite fifty. Yes, because I took a hall you see, there was no room in t
he house, neither in our house or the - missus's house, for the guests - took a hall
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You didn't have a honeymoon, you didn't have a couple of days at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no, no. Just started going back to work next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did you live after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
I lived with the wife's mother 'til I got a house of me own and I didn't live with the wife's mother very long. Just a matter of - about three or four weeks. Got a house of me won.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You rented a house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Rented, yes, rented a house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That was in Jarrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did you live there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did I live there? Oh I lived there about - say about four year, lived in that house in Jarrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That would bring you up nearly to the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - 1914 - yes, yes it did. The war was 1914/1918 you see. Yes, that's it, about the end of the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How old was your wife when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She was the same age as myself. Yes. Twenty-two. She's younger like, about - you know, just about two or three month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You said she was working as a general servant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In a private house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In a private house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Had she had any other jobs before that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No, as soon as she got o
ld enough - she started to work there as a general servant. She was too young to work anywhere else before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did she carry on working after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Has she had any jobs at all since she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not even any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I wouldn't let her work, I was like that, me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Right bossy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Aye. I'm the boss. I'm working - I'm working, that's enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What do you think she felt about her job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why didn't she like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well she didn't like because the money was no use and she was only getting three and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not as much as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, not as much as me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Two sons and one daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were any born in the first four years of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who was born in the first four years?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The oldest son.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you know what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Eeh now I couldn't tell you that, but I know he was born during the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 About how long after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, it'd be about - twelve or thirteen month I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And was the second one born fairly soon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He was born - he'd be born about a year after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So there were two born in the first two or three years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, that was so, then the daughter was born about five year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So one was born about 1915 or 1916?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And one about 1917 or 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That's so, that's so, that's so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were they born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any medical help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did - what kind of medical help did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Doctor. Doctor, own doctor for all the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you help during the birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How soon did your wife - get out of bed after the boys were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She'd be quite a fortnight. That was the rule in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 At the end of the fortnight was she up for the whole day immediately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, she was - yes, she'd be up for the whole day, she was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 hard worker
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  my missus and she like to get stuck in cleaning the house or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you manage whist she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh well I was always managed all right you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did any of your relations or neighbours help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. Nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You looked after the house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I looked after the house, that's so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You didn't have a nurse or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much did you have to do with your children when they were very small babies under twelve months old, what kind of jobs did you 
do if any, like feeding them and bathing them and changing nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
The boys - the boys I used to - bath them when the missus - maybe she would - busy doing something else, would you mind bathing - and I bathed, would bath the boys but never bathed t
he girl. And - the boys used to like me to bath them because I used to play with them and rub them down and all this that and other. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you change nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Get them to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh get them to sleep many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever get up in the night when they were crying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Oh yes. Get up and - used to warm a pan of milk on the gas, two o'clock in the morning or one o'clock in the morning, hold it over the gas, a pan of milk and put it in the bottle to give them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When they were small babies did you used to take them out without your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Take them out in the pram. When they got a bit older I used to take them out on me bike, I had a bike. Put that - put a front seat on the crossbar you know and put them on there, I used to take them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much of your wages did you give to your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I always gave my wife all me wages always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What were you earning, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, I would - when I was first married I was earning about - thirty-seven shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did that increase at all during the war or did it say the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well it increased - very little during the first world war, it increased - it come up to about two pound or three - I give all that to me wife and she used to give me pocket money back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not as - not as much as she got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How many rooms were there in the house you lived in, the first house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Three rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Three. Oh no, there was four rooms. There were three bedrooms and a kitchen. Three bedrooms and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was the washing done at home or did you send it out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 It was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you or your wife make or mend any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Now, the wife used to make the child - the children's clothes. But our own clothes we used to buy them. She used to make the child - kids clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you used to buy new clothes or second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 New clothes. Always new clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you remember where you bought them, or where she bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. She bought my clothes at a place in Jarrow called Gibbon and Knox. It was a big store - a big - shop. And her clot
hes, she used to buy them at - a place called Younghusbands, that was another - pretty big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 store}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  in Jarrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was there a special time of the year when you bought clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, just bought them when we needed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about shoes, did you do any shoe mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Soling and heeling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, yes, myself, yes, myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you buy new shoes or secondhand shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 New shoes, all new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 At the same place as your other clothes or different shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Different shops.
