\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, they had - some jam and bread and cheese or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they have that at the same time as you or before you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well they were generally out when I came in but - they were playing you see but if they'd come in and see me getting anything to eat, you know, they - give us a slice of bread}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  You see, and mother would give them a sli
ce of bread and - they would ask for a cup of tea as well and she'd give them a cup of tea and that was that. Didn't all sit down together, they used to be playing you see, they'd come in and see you eating and they - have their bread and go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What time did you have your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Mostly about five o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you have anything different for dinner or anything different at night on Saturdays or Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 On Sundays you had but not - not Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you have on Sundays then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well used to have - sometimes you'd have a chicken for a change you see, or sometimes a small goose for a change. Then sometimes }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  just like the same you see, beef. Beef. Beefsteak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Sundays tea, well they generally had the best china out and - and - spice cake and - biscuits and - things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you or your wife make any of these things, bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. The wife made -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The missus made jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Pickles? Pickled onions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes, the wife used to pickle them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you used to grow any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember any of the things you used to grow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes, I used to grow - gooseberries. - Black current berries, redcurrant berries, apples. But they were very sour like but we used to grow them. That was about all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you used to buy vegetables and other fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well we
 used to buy them but I also used to grow cabbages, you see, but of course, you never grow enough you see, in the wintertime you used to have to go and buy some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever buy any tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No. No. Always fresh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you keep any hens, pigs, or goats, rabbits, anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes, I kept hens. For a short while and - used to lay eggs and we used to fresh egg for our breakfast. Then I kept rabbits. I was always fond of animals. I kept rabbits and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you eat the rabbits you kept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. But I didn't kill them, I used to take them to the butcher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who looked after your hens and rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You must have had a big back yard or garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We had a rather big garden at the back of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember about how many times a week you had meat, you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, well - meself we had meat every day. Every day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, corned beef. That's - that's tinned meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever get any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your wife ever go short so that you or the children could have more food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not what I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you used to get larger helpings than the rest of the family at mealtimes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well, yes - the missus always seen that I got the big plate like and - the youngsters of course weren't as big as me and they got the smaller plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you allow your children to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could they choose what they wanted to eat or did they have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh - they would choose what they wanted to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you or your wife say to them if they left some food uneaten on their plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 We used to ask them why they left it. Were they ill
. Well why have you left it. Why didn't you eat it. And they say, because we - we can't eat it. Why? Because we're full. And that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Didn't make any more fuss about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, they didn't make no more fuss about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When they wanted something such as the salt did they have to wait until it was offered to them or did they ask for it to be passed?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They asked, please pass the salt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about second helpings, were they able to ask for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes. Said, I haven't had enough mum, give us a bit more. Get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you teach them to hold their knife and fork in a special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, they hadn't to put their elbows on the tables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could they bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any kind of toys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, any kind of toy
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When and how could they get away from the table, when they'd finished or did they have wait until everyone had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They wait 'til everyone had finished 
and they would ask, please may I leave the table? And if we said, certainly, yes, you can't take it with you, it's too big. They would leave them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did everybody who was in the house sit down at the table together for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Usually, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you all have your own places or did you sit where you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, we all had our own places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who used to serve the meal and in what order were the members of the family served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 My wife used to serve the meal and she used to serve me f
irst, then she'd serve the oldest son and the youngest son and the - the daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Then herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Herself - herself last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When the children were too young to feed themselves how were they fed and where did they sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well they used to -
 they had a high chair and a little table on the high chair. And their mother used to put their food on a place in front of them and give them a spoon and - when she was getting her dinner she would watch that they got their dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When hour children were young did you feel that there was a right way and wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you and your wife have the same ideas about bringing them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you talk about the things you would do and things you wouldn't do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes, oh yes, oh the missus and I used to talk and - the missus'd just say to me that - Ronnie would like a bicycle. And so I'd say, how do you know? And, he - he's asked me. Do you think he should have one? Well I would say,
 I think he's a bit young, you see. She said, why? Well - it's very dangerous, I says, he'd get on the bicycle and run down a bit of a bank in the street there, I says, and get on to the main road I says, he might get knocked down. I said, he shouldn't ha
ve a bicycle 'til he's older. Well, she says, I see your point. And he wouldn't get a bicycle 'til he was older, and that was that, she'd see that quite sensible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was there anyone you and your wife used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 missus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  had a neighbour what was older than her and - she used to go and - talk to her and ask her what she thought. She'd say, so and so got the measles, you know, and I wouldn't know - I - I didn't know. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 she\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  go to her - a neighbour what was older than her and ask her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Your mother was her dead of course but was your wife's mother alive when your own children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - very - maybe about - once a week or tw
ice a week, you don't like mother-in-laws you know, I don't, I don't know whether you do or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did she used to come to your house once a week then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ask her advice about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not me. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Do you think that you and she had the same ideas about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, she had different ideas. She was more old fashioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you give me any examples?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - she would have the children in - eight o'clock at night or something like that and had 
to be in bed at a certain time and - specially the girls, you see, well I was never like that. I says, if the girl's going to do anything wrong, she can do it anytime, never mind after ten o'clock or after eleven o'clock. She'll do it any time. I said, ju
st let them have their own way, let them come in when they like and that was that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever have anyone to look after you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you think it was important to give your children affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, I thought that was important, give them affection and I also - another thing was important - see that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 they\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 obedient. Because I thought children was very vindictive you know, they would want their own way. Well I stressed the point that - they couldn't have their own way. Such -
 such as the two - the two sons, now the young son he would - go out to a cricket pitch and start playing cricket and all this that and other and his brother which is older than him, would have a mate and he wanted to go and play on that cricket pitch you
 
see. So the young 'un would sit down and he would say, I'm not getting off. I'm not getting off, you're not going to play, I was here first, and - all this business you see. So I used to interfere and then I used to go and tell him you see, I said, no, yo
u
're just trying to be a big lad, I says, you're - well he says, I was on the pitch before them. But, I says, you're just playing by yourself. I said, he's got a - a pal here. Put the wickets up and he's going to bat at this end and his pal's - the other o
ne at the other end, I said, you're only just one bat just playing yourself. And I said to him, now, come on, get up and let them play. And that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you fairly strict then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well strict to a certain extent in just little things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about regard for their safety, were you always interfering so they wouldn't get hurt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes, oh yes, if - I was always very strict about that. Well that went - just goes to show you when he asked his mother for a bike you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the food they used to eat, did you think you had to provide certain kinds of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, not - not when they were in good health but if they were ill and had to have a certain food well - you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you try and get your children to share their worries with you when they wee small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes, always told them about any troubles, tell your mother or your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you want them to behave towards you, did they have to be very respectful or pally or what?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well we just - treat them as - just as they were our friends you know, our pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you let them join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Mm-hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you bring them up to consider was important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They hadn't to tell any lies and - they had to 
- go to Sunday school. And when they got older they'd go to church. Brought them all up in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 If another child hurt them did you encourage them to hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Always. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there any other children that you discouraged your own children from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well if I knew any children used bad language you see, and I heard them, I would say don't play with that boy. He swears, he's using bad language, that's - naughty that. Yes. T
ell them not to play with them and - and they wouldn't - and - they wouldn't play with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any other children they weren't allowed to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any children who was dirty, I wouldn't allow them to play with. You know, that never washed their 
face and washed their hands and things like that. And - in my day a lot of children, their parents couldn't afford - boots nor nothing, they used to go about in their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 bare feet}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  and this that and the other. Well, if anyone fetched a little boy into our house with his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 bare feet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 - I used to ask him is your father working? And this that and the other. No. And - if - his feet were the same size of many of my sons I would say to the sons, have you not got an old pair of shoes you could give your little friend? An
d of course - there - oh yes, I've got a pair of shoes I don't like, you see, and they would give them to the kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You were saying earlier that you didn't like Catholics very much when you were a boy, did you mind your children playing with Catholics?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes, I didn't like them playing with Catholics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And you tried to stop them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you used to say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I used to say to them - I wouldn't play with - with that boy or with a girl and - I said, can't picture - the
y used to say, what's the difference you see. Well I says, I think it's a bit of a prejudice, I says, because my father, I says, he was born in Dublin but he was a Protestant and - there was some Catholics met him coming out of the Protestant church one S
unday and got a hold of him, they were bigger than him like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did they say when you told them that story?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 They just - well the - they just said the same as me - they done that did they? And, oh well if they're going to do that to me I - won'
t have anything to do with them, you see, so they wouldn't have anything to do with them. But, mind in later life, I found out - I don't - I'm not prejudiced against Catholics but - the only fault I have with Catholics is that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 they\rquote ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  do anything for mon
ey. You see, in the Catholic church they'll have - play bingo and have lotteries and all this sort of thing for money, do anything for money. And when they've confessed to the Father their sins they'll just go out of church and go to the boozer and get dr
unk and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 maybe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 go with women or anything like that and they'll go back again to the Father and confess. You see, and the Father's just sitting in the - in the pulpit or wherever he is, just laughing his head off at them. Right? Right? Yes, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 If your children did something that you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well I would tell them that I didn't approve of that and don't do it anymore, you see Now if they did do it again and I - found them - found out about it, I used to put them over me knee and give them a good smacking on the behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 With an iron bar or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, with me hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you hit them often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 Very, very, very very seldom. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your wife used to hit them at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Very seldom no, she use
d to tell me. She never hit them at all. She'd tell me, no - she'd tell me when I come home from work, say, so and so's been naughty. What's he done? Where is he? He's out. Oh well, when he comes in - when I come in I asked him why he done that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember any particular occasion when you had to hit one of your children when they were fairly - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 young}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Mostly the daughter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Could you stick to the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When the eldest one was about four or five years old, can you think of anything that happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I never had any - no occasion to hit the boys - never had any trouble at all with the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Would you say that your children received the ideas that they had about how to behave from both you and your 
wife or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 missus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  played the most important part with the children. She telled them what to do and what not to do and if they wouldn't do it she used to come and tell me. Then of course they 
were more afraid of me than what they was of their mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 But you were just backing up your wife really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, I backed her - oh yes, I backed - backed up the missus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. Yes, when the children had a birthday the missus would always make them a birthday cake. And - if they were two, three, four or five she'd put the candles on and she'd ice the cake and have a proper birthday. And they would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 ask}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  their mother if they could have their friends in for the birthday party and their mother, yes. They had a birthday party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they get presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Used to - the kids used to fetch some presents, little bits of things. Sending birthday cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you give them presents then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember anything that you did with your wife and children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. We used to - well on Christmas Eve we used to fill all their stockings. Put an orange in and - and nuts and sweets i
n all their stockings. And hang the stockings up on the - side of the bed and - when they woke up they used to be highly delighted with their stockings and their toy. Used to buy them toys and that, and they used to be highly delighted with it and - when 
they come to get their dinner and that they had a special dinner at Christmas Day for them and - I think that was - a Christmas tree and all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you all go out anywhere, go to church or the pictures or anything like that on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 Christmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, we just the - were - stop in the house you know and have a bit of a party in the house Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no one could play, we had a piano like but - the missus could play the piano but none of the children would ever learn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She was the only musician was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, and they - I'll tell you, the oldest lad, he used to have a Jews }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13312755\charrsid15818556 
harp}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 , have you seen them have you, he used to have one of them and played that.
