\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What card games did you like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Mostly - whist. Or nap. That was about all I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Any music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, no music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you rent your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did you think about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I thought he was a decent sort of a chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In the place where you lived when you first got married who were the most importan
t people, who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well the doctor I think. The doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you used to meet the doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes, I often met the doctor and he was a - he was a good friend of mine, the doctor. And - the police, impo
rtant people, I think the police was important people and all there at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why do you think the doctor and the police were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - if there was anyone ill, you see, well - you didn't know what was the matter with them and that w
as important you had to go and see the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Can you remember in the early years of your marriage who the shopkeepers used to associate with, who they spent their time with, was it the same as when you were a boy, they kept themselves to themselves or did you notice any changes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I think they're just the same, kept theirself to yourself. About the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And the clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well, yes - the clergymen, they just seemed to be the same to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 The teacher? The school teachers? No, just about the same I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 You wouldn't know any farmers would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about me employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who did they used to associate with, spend their time with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I couldn't tell you that now. No, I couldn't tell you who the employers spent their time with. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you say what kind of people went to church in the place where you lived when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes - the people who went to church were mostly - business people, people who had businesses of their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And what about the Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well I never had anything to do with them, I don't know, whether they went to church or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the chapel people then? Were they any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, they were just about the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Business people do you mean? You don't think the labourers and workers generally went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 I don't think that they believed in church myself, the working class labourers and this that and another, used to think more o
r going into the boozer and getting drunk than of going to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did all the working people who lived around you have the same standard of living or could you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh I could say they were different, they didn't have the same - they didn't have the same food as us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What kind of groups were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well there was labourers you see - and labourers used to work at glass furnaces and this that and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you describe a family that you knew in the first few years of your marriage who were labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes. Yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 
There was a chap lived opposite, me, he was a labourer and he used to work at the glass furnaces and - they had - different food altogether and his missus couldn't cook very well and h
e used to go to the fish shop - penny fish and a penn'orth of chips and - and they used to have that for their dinner. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
And - for their tea they'd go to the - cake shop and get a penny cake or something like that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 you see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
, she never baked any bread, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What other groups were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well there was - they weren't all the same, the - I knew another labouring chap, now they were different. You see, his wife would - you know, used to bake bread and bake Yorkshire pudding and - give 'em a proper dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did these two men do the same kind of work as each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did they live in the same kind of house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Lived next door to one another, same sort of house, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 So you can't say really there's any typical labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, that's right, that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were these two labourers any different from any other people, from yourself for example?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well yes - yes. Now - they didn't keep their children as clean. You see, no. And - the children come in
to my house and play with my children and - they wouldn't have their ears washed out, you see, their ears used to be, you know, dirty. And their mother must have never washed their ears out you see. And - my missus used to get a hold of them and say, you'
re mother's forgot to wash you this morning, and my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 missus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  used to wash them. Wash their ears out and that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 And - she used - she'd tell them that their pinny was dirty. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
You see, has your mother not put a new pinny on you this morning? Of course, the kid said, me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
 - hasn't got a new pinny. Well she'd say, why hasn't she washed that one, you see? She says, I don't know, I don't think she's got any soap you see, and things like that. And - my missus used to take her pinny off and wash it. And - then she w
ould go to the lady and - I hope you don't mind me - washing your little girl's pinny. And - oh - certainly not, she says, to tell you the truth, she says - I haven't any soap in the house. You see. How's that? Well, she says, my husband doesn't get the s
ame wage as your husband you see, and there you are. And so my missus would turn round, she says, he only gets a pound more than your husband you see. Oh well, a pound's a pound you know - and that would get them talking you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were there any working class families that were better off than you or different in any superior way that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Yes. I worked - yes, I can tell you - a tale about that. One chap and - he was a chap that never work, and he was a - he was a fitter by trade and he was better dressed than what I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
This was in Jarrow. In Jarrow. And he was better dressed than I was. And - I used to - Jimmy they called him, Jimmy McNee. I says, are you not working then? So he says, no, he says, it's only that mugs that work. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Where did he get his money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
He used to - he told me that he used to - get stuff on the hire purchase and never pay for it. And that was that, he used to have better clothes on than me. Go to his house, lovely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 furniture}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  and all this, this that and other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about his family, were they any different than your kids and your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
No. No. The - I - I never seen his wife, I seen the kids but I never seen his wife. But I tell you, he was - I used to, you know, be surprised
 see him coming along the street all toffed up and he wasn't working. And of course I was inquisitive you know and I says, you've got a better suit on than me. He says, I tell you it's mugs that work. And that's the way you get the clothes, you can get th
em on patman. I say, you've got to pay the patman. Aye, he says when you've got anything, he says, but I never ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
. There you are.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Of these groups of working people that you've mentioned was there any group that felt itself superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well the fellow at the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well - you know, there's some of your neighbours - the - give you the impression, whether they was or not I don't know but they gave you the impression that they were - superior to you. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were these usually labourers families or craftsmen's families or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, they most - they were mostly labouring people, labour - labouring class people. Thought better than you, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were some families considered rough and some respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Can you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers as far as being respectable and rough is concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, well I've always found that the majority of craftsmen, they are different people altogether to the - to the
 labouring class. They take more - more responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 In these early years when you were first married did you have to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did that bother you, what did you think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well - what I thought about it
 - I thought that - our wages should have been higher you see. And - I used to do all I could for to try and - get the weekend in you see, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 for to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  get more money for the - because in them days - they weren't paid holidays, you see. The race week you got - a
bout fifteen days holiday. You see, nothing coming in. well how did you manage you see, and it wasn't a holiday, it was a worry, you see, and that used to worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you ever ill or out of work for the first few years that you were married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What difference did it make to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Oh it made a big difference because - my children got the mumps. Now I got the it off the children, and I got the mumps and that was the worst illness I ever had in me life you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long were you off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Oh I was off work about ten weeks - seriously, yes. Then of course in them days there was no National Health or anything. The doctor had to be paid. You see, and of course - all that money had to be - we - we had no money then and I had to
 - when I went to work all that money had to be saved up for the paying the doctor you see. No, we were all - struggling and trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How did you manage, what difference did it make to the food you had or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well it didn't make 
any difference to that because - I - me father, he - he was in business you see and I used to go along and mention it to him and - he would give you a pound or two you see, a couple of pound for you Bob, that'll see you thorough and anything you want just
 come and - it's here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you only ill the once during these first few years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well, that's - yes - I've had coughs and colds and this that and another but that' nothing, that - I was only - that - the mumps - terrible thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Were you ever out of work in the first four or five years after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, I'm never out of work in me life. Because if I couldn't get a job at me own trade, I would take a labouring job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, there was no - no help then, they wouldn't give you any. Well, I never asked none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was your eldest boy's first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me eldest boy's first job was selling pies. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did he do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How lo
ng did he do that for? Oh - I think he said to eat more than what he used to sell. But anyway that was his first job and I think he was there about - oh - say about three month or something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What jobs has he had since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Then he got a job - working in a grocery shop, taking - taking the groceries out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 That would be for about - four or five month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And - then I got him a job - for to serve his time, be an electrician. And - he served his t
ime to be an electrician and - I learnt them where I was working, I was working at the time I was working at Welders Limited and I fetched him into where I was working and show - showed him how the electric welding and this that and other. And he learnt e
lectric welding. Then he got a job electric welding. Then he worked his way up and - he's now like supervisor to electric welding you see at English Electric in Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about the younger son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Well the youngest one, I got him a job ink - h
e done the same, like he worked in a grocers shop and all this that and another but when he got older I got him a job, I used to know a J.P. in Newcastle, and I got him a job through this J.P. in - the gas company. And I wanted him to be a fitter in the g
a
s - a gas fitter. But - with his brother being an electric welder and getting more money than him, when I was away at Colchester - he left his job at the gas company and got a job - at Swann and Hunters as a welder, you see, 'cos his brother was getting m
ore money than him and so they're both welders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Has he got a posh job now like the elder brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Is he a supervisor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, he's not a supervisor but he's - he's got a good job at the Caterpillar at Rugby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What's his job called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He's - he's electric welder. At Caterpillar.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about your daughter, what was her first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now with the daughter her first job was - a housemaid in Harrogate. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did she do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh she was there for about three or four months, she didn't like it and she come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And then what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She just helped her mother in the house 'til she met her young man and she got married and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 And since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She got married and - she - her husband wasn't making enough money for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He was an electrician, at the Theatre Royal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Your daughter worked in Harrogate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She worked in Harrogate, yes, as a general maid. Then she didn't like it and she come home. And - just worked 
in the house with her mother. Then she started courting, young man. And she got married. And - she didn't - she - she seemed to think that - her husband didn't get enough money so she got a job herself and they were both working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What was her job after she got married then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She got a job with Newcastle Breweries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was she a manageress from the start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
She was manageress from the - no, no, she wasn't, she was barmaid. She was only a harmaid about - couple of month and - they made her manageress of the bar and she's been manageress ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Her husband has continued as an electrician has he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, but she got shot of her husband. Because - in the pub - what she was in - she lived on the premises and he was working at the theatr
e and she was missing money. And - of course in a pub he pound notes and five pound notes is generally put in with a pint glass you see at the sideboard in the pub and - she was short in her stock of the - mater of - four or five or six pound and she blam
e
d the barmaids for it, you see. And - of course the barmaids pleaded innocent, you see, they never touch this and all this that and another. So she kept her eyes open and when her husband was going out to work she must have had her suspicions, when her hu
s
band was going out to work - to the theatre, she - lay in bed for a little bit then she got up and as he was going out she's come down the stairs and as he was going out he slipped his hand in the - where the money was in the pint glass. Couple of quit ou
t and he showed it in his pocket and she caught him you see. And of course they had a row and she threw him out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Has she married again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, she hasn't married again. But she's knocking about with a - a young chap. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She's not working in the pub now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No, she's retired now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
My brother? Yes, well I - as I tell - as I tell you, we had a business in Jarrow and of course, when me father died he left the business to me brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did he continue with that business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He continued with the business. 'Til he wasn't the same sort of a man as me father like, he - but he looked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556  after}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  the business as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 best}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  he could. Now he took ill. And I never had much to do with him myself. And I got told that the shop
 was shut. In - in Marrow. And I was working at Palmer Trowler at me own trade and everything you see, so I went over for to see what was the matter. And - I knocked and knocked and knocked and knocked and the shop was shut and knocked at the door.; They 
lived in the back of the shop you see. And he let us in. Well he was half drunk. And when I got in - he had - oh - three or four empty bottles of brandy lying about, he'd just been lying there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7698975\charrsid15818556 drinking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556  brandy. And of course, I says, this won't do. So, I say
s, you'd better come and live with me. So I fetch him into my house and - I give up my job and I went and looked after the shop. But I had a talk to him before that. I - and - he told me that - the shop was - paying all right and all this that and the oth
er. Well anyway, I give my mob up with Palmer Trowler, I went and looked after the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 For how long was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Now half a minute and I'll tell you. I looked after the shop and - I used to sharpen saws, sharpen scissors and do all the work and th
at had to be done. And - then - I got word from - Town Council that I was under compulsory purchase and it had to come down, you see. And - I had to give it up and - they pulled it down band built these wonderful flats - and I left that. Right. Just my lu
ck.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 How long did you spend in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Me, about - be only about twelve month, and they - they pulled it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did your brother work again after he'd come to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 No. No, he come to - I fetched him to our house and the missus looked after him and - he died - he died at our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Was that William or John?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 William.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What about John, what jobs did he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Oh John, he - he worked in the Co-operative Society as a grocer. Worked as a grocer and - he got called up duri
ng the first world war and - he got bayoneted in the thing, he was never right after that. He - come home and after he come home he went back to work but he died. He died with T.B. in the leg and it was with this bayonet would in his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What jobs did your sisters have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 
Well, Harriet, she got married and - away, but me other sister she never got married. She was a - she - she lived with me brother in the - in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She helped in the shop and did the housework did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She - she did the housework and helped me brother in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 She never had any mobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Never had any job or anything no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Did Harriet ever have any jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Not that I know of, no, not as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 He was a pitman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10813999 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 What grade, do you know what he did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4870305 RA  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11413802\charrsid15818556 Yes, he was a hewer, hewer down the pit.
\par }}